\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ74617 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74619 told \add @Bileam\add*, вҖңPlease come with me to anotherВҰ74628 placeВҰ74627 \add вүҲthat you'll be able to see them from\add*. You won'tВҰ74636 \add be able to\add* see all of \add #them\add*, only the edge \add of that large group\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ74617\add* you'll will curseВҰ74638 \add @Yisrael\add* for me from there.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ74643\add* he tookВҰ74643 \add @Bileam\add* to a fieldВҰ74644 atВҰ74656 the top of \add Mt.\add* PisgahВҰ74649, and he builtВҰ74650 sevenВҰ74651 altars and offered up a bullВҰ74654 and a ram onВҰ74656 \add each\add* altarВҰ74656.
\p
\v 15 Bileam saidВҰ74658 to \add вүҲthe king\add*, вҖңYou standВҰ74662 here beside your burntВҰ74666 offeringВҰ74666, while I \add вүҲgo over there so\add* \add Yahweh\add* \add вүҲcan meet me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ74671 YahwehВҰ74672 met withВҰ74678 Bileam and \add вүҲgave him a message\add* and told \add >him\add*, вҖңGo back to BalakВҰ74683, and \add вүҲgive him that message\add*.вҖқ
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ74687\add* he \add вүҲreturned\add* to him where he was standingВҰ74690 with the leadersВҰ74694 from MoavВҰ74695 beside the altar, andВҰ74687 BalakВҰ74699 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhat did YahwehВҰ74703 say?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ74705 \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲgave his speech\add*,
\q1 вҖң\add вүҲLook here\add*, BalakВҰ74709, andВҰ74705 listenВҰ74711.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲPay attention\add* to me, son of Tsipor.
\q1
\v 19 GodВҰ74718 doesn't lie because he's not a humanВҰ74717 being,
\q1 вүҲand he's not a mortal who might changeВҰ74723 his mind.
\q1 Whatever he's saidВҰ74725, he'll do it.
\q1 вүҲAnything he \add вүҲpromised\add*, he'll make it \add вүҲhappen\add*.
\q1
\v 20 Listen, I'veВҰ74734 receivedВҰ74734 \add a command\add* to bless.
\q1 вүҲ\add Yes,\add* he's \add decided to\add* bless and I can'tВҰ74736 reverse itВҰ74737.
\p
\v 21 \add @YahwehВҰ74749\add* hasn't \add вүҲconsidered\add* hardship for Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 вүҲand he hasn't seenВҰ74746 troubleВҰ74747 for YisraelВҰ74748 \add (IsraelВҰ74748)\add*.
\q1 His godВҰ74750 Yahweh is withВҰ74743 \add @that people group\add*,
\q1 and the king's shoutВҰ74752 is over him.
\q1
\v 22 GodВҰ74756 brought them out of EgyptВҰ74758 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*,
\q1 вҶ’\add giving them strength\add* like a wild bull's hornsВҰ74759.
\q1
\v 23 \add вүҲNo,\add* there's no spell against Yakov,
\q1 вүҲand no divinationВҰ74770 against Yisrael.
\q1 \add People\add* will talk aboutВҰ74772 Yakov/Yisrael,
\q1 вҶ’\add saying look\add* what GodВҰ74779 has doneВҰ74778.
\q1
\v 24 That population stands up like a lionessВҰ74784,
\q1 вүҲand like a lionВҰ74786, it liftsВҰ74787 itselfВҰ74787 up.
\q1 It won'tВҰ74788 lie down untilВҰ74790 it's devourВҰ74792 its prey
\q1 and drunk the bloodВҰ74794 of thoseВҰ74796 it killed.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ74799 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74800 \add вүҲscolded\add* Bileam, вҖңEven \add вүҲif you won'tВҰ74807\add* curse them, definitely don'tВҰ74807 \em bless\em* them!вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңDidn't I \add already\add* tell youВҰ74823,вҖқ BileamВҰ74816 answeredВҰ74815 BalakВҰ74820, вҖң\add вүҲthat I can only pronounce what YahwehВҰ74829 tells me to\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Bileam's third prophecy
\rem /s1 Balaam's Third Prophecy; Balaam's Third Oracle
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ74833 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74834 told Bileam, вҖңCome \add вүҲwith me\add*. I'll takeВҰ74841 you to anotherВҰ74845 placeВҰ74844. Perhaps it will \add вүҲpleasedВҰ74840\add* God \add вүҲif\add* you curseВҰ74850 \add #them\add* for me from thereВҰ74852.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ74854\add* BalakВҰ74855 tookВҰ74854 \add *him\add* to the top of \add MtВҰ74858.\add* PeorВҰ74860 \add вүҲthatВҰ74861 faces down\add* to the wilderness,
\v 29 and \add again\add* Bileam told \add *him\add*, вҖңBuild seven altarsВҰ74877 and prepareВҰ74878 seven bullsВҰ74882 and seven rams for me \add вүҲhere\add*.вҖқ
\v 30 \add вүҲSoВҰ74886\add* BalakВҰ74887 \add вүҲfollowed those instructions\add* and offered a bullВҰ74892 and a ram onВҰ74894 \add each\add* altarВҰ74894.
\c 24
\rem /s1 Balaam's Third Oracle
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲBy now,\add* Bileam \add вүҲhad realisedВҰ74896\add* that YahwehВҰ74901 wanted to blessВҰ74902 \add вүҲthe Israelis\add*, \add вүҲso\add* he didn'tВҰ74906 \add вүҲuse his usual divinations\add* \add вүҲbutВҰ74896 instead, he just looked towards\add* the wildernessВҰ74917.
\v 2 He \add вүҲlooked up\add* andВҰ74920 sawВҰ74925 YisraelВҰ74928 \add вүҲin their tents laid out by tribeВҰ74930\add*. ThenВҰ74920 God's spiritВҰ74933 came onto him,
\v 3 andВҰ74936 he \add вүҲmade his pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖң\add This is\add* the declaration of Bileam, son of BeorВҰ74942вҖ”
\q1 вүҲthe utteranceВҰ74936 of a manВҰ74944 whose eyes are open.
\q1
\v 4 The declaration of someone who heard God's messageВҰ74948,
\q1 вүҲsomeone who seesВҰ74956 the all-powerful one's visionВҰ74954,
\q1 who bows to the ground with his eyesВҰ74959 \add вүҲwide open\add*.
\q1
\v 5 \add вүҲYes\add* Yakov, your tentsВҰ74964 look goodВҰ74963.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲYes\add* YisraelВҰ74967, \add вүҲthe placesВҰ74966 where you're livingВҰ74966\add*:
\q1
\v 6 They stretchВҰ74970 out like a riverbed.
\q1 вүҲLike gardensВҰ74971 beside a riverВҰ74973.
\q1 Like \add вүҲpalms\add* thatВҰ74970 YahwehВҰ74976 has plantedВҰ74975,
\q1 вүҲLike cedarВҰ74977 \add trees\add* beside the watersВҰ74980.
\q1
\v 7 Water will \add вүҲspill over the top of\add* his bucketsВҰ74985,
\q1 and his \add вүҲdescendants will flow out\add* like waterВҰ74984.
\q1 \add @Yisrael's\add* kingВҰ74991 will be greater than \add KingВҰ74991\add* AgagВҰ74990,
\q1 and his kingdomВҰ74993 will become honoured.
\q1
\v 8 GodВҰ74995 is bringingВҰ74996 him \add here\add* from EgyptВҰ74997
\q1 \add with power\add* like the hornsВҰ74998 of a wild bullВҰ74999.
\q1 He'll \add вүҲdevastate\add* those nationsВҰ75002 \add вүҲthat oppose him\add*.
\q1 He'll breakВҰ75005 theirВҰ75004 bonesВҰ75004, and hisВҰ74996 arrowsВҰ75006 will pierce them.
\q1
\v 9 He crouchedВҰ75009вҖ”lying down like a lionВҰ75011 or a lionessВҰ75012.
\q1 Who will rouseВҰ75014 himВҰ75014?
\q1 Those who bless, you will be blessed,
\q1 ^\add вүҲbut\add* those who curse you, will be cursed.\x + \xo 24:9: a \xt Gen 49:9; \xo b \xt Gen 12:3.\x*
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ75020 \add King\add* BalakВҰ75023 \add вүҲgot very angry\add* with Bileam, and he banged his handsВҰ75030 togetherВҰ75027 and saidВҰ75031 \add angrily\add*, вҖңI called you to \em curseВҰ75036\em* my enemiesВҰ75037, and \add вүҲblast you\add*, you'veВҰ75040 actuallyВҰ75041 blessedВҰ75040 \add <them\add* threeВҰ75043 timesВҰ75044 \add now\add*!
\v 11 \add вүҲNow get back to where you came from\add*! I said that I'd honour you \add вүҲvery well\add*, butВҰ75046 man, YahwehВҰ75058 has kept you from any honour!вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ75061\add* Bileam \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңDidn't I also tell the messengersВҰ75070 that youВҰ75073 sentВҰ75073 to me that
\v 13 even if you gave me a houseВҰ75085 full of goldВҰ75087 andВҰ75087 silverВҰ75086, I wouldn't be able \add вүҲto say anything other than what Yahweh tells me\add*вҖ”whether goodВҰ75096 or evil? Whatever Yahweh tells me, that's what I have to say.
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Prophecies
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ75107 yes,\add* I'llВҰ75108 go back home now, \add вүҲbutВҰ75107 first, allow me\add* to tell you what thatВҰ75113 people group will do to your people in the future.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Prophecies; Balaam's Fourth Oracle
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ75121 Bileam gave this pronouncement to Balak,
\q1 вҖң\add This is\add* the declaration of Bileam, son of BeorВҰ75127вҖ”
\q1 вүҲthe utteranceВҰ75121 of a manВҰ75129 whose eyes are open.
\q1
\v 16 The statement from someone who hearsВҰ75134 God's messages,
\q1 вүҲand the one who receives knowledgeВҰ75139 from the highest one,
\q1 who seesВҰ75143 visionsВҰ75141 from the powerful one.
\q1 вүҲThe one who fallsВҰ75144 to his knees with his eyesВҰ75146 opened.
\q1
\v 17 I seeВҰ75151 him, \add вүҲbut\add* not now.
\q1 вүҲI'll look at him, \add вүҲbut\add* he's not close.
\q1 A starВҰ75155 has marchedВҰ75154 out from Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 вүҲand a staff has risen from YisraelВҰ75159 \add (IsraelВҰ75159)\add*.
\q1 He will crushВҰ75160 Moav's cornersВҰ75161,
\q1 вүҲand destroyВҰ75163 all of Shet's \add (Seth's)\add* descendantsВҰ75166.
\q1
\v 18 EdomВҰ75171 will become \add &their\add* possession,
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲas will\add* his enemy, SeirВҰ75175.
\q1 YisraelВҰ75177 \add вүҲwill project\add* strengthВҰ75179.
\q1
\v 19 A ruler \add will come\add* from Yakov,
\q1 вҶ’and destroyВҰ75183 the city's survivorsВҰ75184.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Oracles
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ75187 \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲlooked towards\add* AmalekВҰ75190 andВҰ75187 \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңAmalek is the firstВҰ75194 of the nationsВҰ75195,
\q2 ^\add вүҲbut\add* itsВҰ75197 endВҰ75197 will be destructionВҰ75199.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ75201 he \add вүҲlooked towards\add* the Kenites and \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңYour dwellingВҰ75209 is permanent,
\q1 вүҲand your nestВҰ75212 is set inВҰ75211 the cliffs.
\q1
\v 22 but you Kenites will be destroyedВҰ75218
\q1 when Ashhur \add ?(the Assyrians)\add* takeВҰ75224 you captiveВҰ75224.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ75226 \add finally,\add* \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңOh dear, who can \add вүҲsurvive\add* when GodВҰ75233 does \add all\add* that?
\q1
\v 24 Ships will come from the KittimВҰ75237 coastВҰ75236 \add (Cyprus)\add*,
\q1 and they'll \add вүҲdamage\add* AsshurВҰ75239 and Ever,
\q1 \add вүҲbutВҰ75235 they themselves\add* will be destroyedВҰ75247 as well.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ75249 Bileam \add вүҲpacked up\add* and went home, and \add King\add* BalakВҰ75256 also went on his wayВҰ75258.
\c 25
\s1 Yisrael worships Baal at Peor
\rem /s1 Moab Seduces Israel; The People of Israel at Peor; Worship of Baal of Peor
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ75265 settled down\add* atВҰ75263 ShittimВҰ75263, and \add вүҲtheir men started sleeping withВҰ75263 womenВҰ75269 from Moav\add*
\v 2 \add вүҲwho thenВҰ75272\add* invitedВҰ75272 them to sacrificesВҰ75274 to their \add вүҲidols\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ75272\add* \add @the IsraelisВҰ75273\add* bowedВҰ75278 down \add to the idols\add* andВҰ75272 ateВҰ75276 \add at the feasts\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ75286 \add when\add* YisraelВҰ75283 consecrated themselves to BaalВҰ75284-PeorВҰ75285, Yahweh'sВҰ75289 angerВҰ75288 burned towards \add *them\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ75292 Yahweh told MoshehВҰ75296, вҖң\add вүҲExecute\add* all the people'sВҰ75303 leaders and \add вүҲdisplay their bodies in broad daylight\add*, and thenВҰ75292 Yahweh'sВҰ75293 \add вүҲangerВҰ75311\add* might turnВҰ75309 back away from YisraelВҰ75314.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ75316\add* MoshehВҰ75317 to Yisrael's judgesВҰ75320, вҖң\add вүҲEach of you must execute your menВҰ75324 who have joinedВҰ75325 others to serve\add* BaalВҰ75326-PeorВҰ75327.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲJust thenВҰ75329, unbelievably,\add* an \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75332\add* manВҰ75330 \add вүҲcame past\add* MoshehВҰ75342 and \add вүҲall the peopleВҰ75347\add* who were \add there outside\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ75353\add* tentВҰ75353 weepingВҰ75351, and he was bringing a Midyanite woman \add вүҲwith him\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ75356\add* Pinehas (son of EleazarВҰ75360, son of Aharon) sawВҰ75356 \add <that\add*, he \add вүҲcame out\add* from amongВҰ75366 the \add вүҲgathered people\add*, grabbed a spearВҰ75369,
\v 8 and followed the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75374\add* man into \add &his\add* tent. He \add вүҲplunged\add* the spear through the two of themвҖ”right through the man and the woman'sВҰ75389 bellyВҰ75392, and \add thus\add*, stoppedВҰ75393 the plagueВҰ75394 \add that had started\add* against the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ75374\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add*, twenty-four thousandВҰ75404 people had \add already\add* diedВҰ75400 from the plagueВҰ75401.
\p
\v 10 Then YahwehВҰ75408 spokeВҰ75407 to MoshehВҰ75411,
\v 11 вҖңAharon's grandson Pinehas has \add вүҲdeflected my angerВҰ75425\add* from the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ75427\add* by \add вүҲdemonstrating my seriousness about theirВҰ75434 behaviour\add*, \add вүҲso now\add* inВҰ75430 my zeal, I won'tВҰ75435 \add вүҲeliminate the Israelis\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* tell him that I'm \add вүҲmaking\add* a peaceВҰ75453 agreementВҰ75452 with him.
\v 13 It'sВҰ75470 an agreementВҰ75459 that gives him and his \add вүҲdescendantsВҰ75457\add* \add вүҲthe rights to be priestsВҰ75460\add* becauseВҰ75462 he was zealousВҰ75464 \add вүҲon his god's behalf\add* and he \add вүҲworked towards removing the guilt\add* of the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ75469\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 The \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75473\add* manВҰ75473 \add вүҲwho was killed\add* with the Midyanite woman was Salu'sВҰ75484 son ZimriВҰ75481, a \add вүҲclan leaderВҰ75485\add* from the Shimeon tribe.
\v 15 The Midyanite womanВҰ75492 \add вүҲwho was killed\add* was Kozbi, the daughterВҰ75496 of TsurВҰ75498, a Midyanite clan leader.
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ75509 told MoshehВҰ75512,
\v 17 вҖң\add вүҲAttack\add* the Midyanites andВҰ75519 \add вүҲdestroy\add* them
\v 18 because they were \add вүҲtreacherously deceivingВҰ75526\add* you all over the matter of Peor and Kozbi, the daughterВҰ75540 of one of their leadersВҰ75542 who was killedВҰ75545 onВҰ75526 the dayВҰ75546 of the plagueВҰ75548 atВҰ75526 \add Mt.\add* Peor.вҖқ
\c 26
\s1 The second census
\rem /s1 The Second Census; A Census of the New Generation; Israel's Second Census
\p
\v 1 After \add the incident of\add* the plague, YahwehВҰ75562 told MoshehВҰ75565 and Aharon's son EleazarВҰ75567 the priestВҰ75571,\x + \xo 26:1-51: \xt Num 1:1-46.\x*
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲCountВҰ75595 all the IsraeliВҰ75582 peopleВҰ75582\add* \add again\add* \add вүҲlisting all those by theirВҰ75590 clans\add* who are twentyВҰ75586 and over, and \add вүҲcapable of going out to battle\add* for YisraelВҰ75584.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ75597\add* there inВҰ75602 the Moav plainsВҰ75602, across the YardenВҰ75606 river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*, MoshehВҰ75598 andВҰ75599 the priestВҰ75600 EleazarВҰ75599 \add вүҲgave these instructions\add* to \add @the people\add*,
\v 4 вҖңYahwehВҰ75616 has orderedВҰ75615 \add *us\add* \add вүҲto list\add* the names of the \add men\add* who cameВҰ75622 out from EgyptВҰ75624 who are twentyВҰ75611 years old or older.
\s1 Reuven's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Reuben
\p
\v 5 Reuven was Yisrael's eldest son, and his descendantsВҰ75629 came via his sons Hanok, PalluВҰ75634,
\v 6 Hetsron, and Karmi.
\v 7 ThoseВҰ75647 clansВҰ75646 added up to 43,730 men.
\v 8 Pallu'sВҰ75659 son was EliavВҰ75660,
\v 9 and Eliav's son were NemuelВҰ75664, Datan, and Aviram. (That was the Datan and Aviram who were the leaders that rebelled\x + \xo 26:9 \xt 16:1-33.\x* against MoshehВҰ75678 and Aharon when they joined Korah'sВҰ75684 rebellion against YahwehВҰ75688.
\v 10 ThenВҰ75690 the earthВҰ75691 \add вүҲsplit open\add* and swallowedВҰ75695 them and KorahВҰ75699. Yahweh had also sent a fireВҰ75703 that consumedВҰ75702 250 men, and theyВҰ75708 became a warningВҰ75709 signВҰ75709.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Korah'sВҰ75713 descendants hadn't diedВҰ75716 \add thenВҰ75711\add*.)
\s1 Shimeon's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Simeon
\p
\v 12 Shimeon's descendantsВҰ75719 came via his sons NemuelВҰ75722, YaminВҰ75725, YakinВҰ75728,
\v 13 ZerahВҰ75734, and ShaulВҰ75735.
\v 14 ThoseВҰ75741 clansВҰ75740 added up to 22,200 men.
\s1 Gad's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Gad
\p
\v 15 Gad'sВҰ75749 descendantsВҰ75748 came via his sons Tsefon, HaggitВҰ75754, ShuniВҰ75757,
\v 16 OzniВҰ75763, Eir,
\v 17 Arod, and AreliВҰ75771.
\v 18 ThoseВҰ75779 clansВҰ75776 added up to 40,500 men.
\s1 Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Judah
\p
\v 19 YehudahВҰ75788 \add (Judah)\add* had two sonsВҰ75787 ErВҰ75789 and OnanВҰ75790 who diedВҰ75791 \add childless\add* in Kenaan.
\v 20 \add *His\add* descendantsВҰ75798 came via his \add other\add* sons ShelahВҰ75802, Perets, andВҰ75797 ZerahВҰ75808.
\v 21 Perets's descendantsВҰ75813 \add came via his sons\add* Hetsron andВҰ75812 HamulВҰ75819.
\v 22 ThoseВҰ75825 clansВҰ75824 added up to 76,500 men.
\s1 Yissakar's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Issachar
\p
\v 23 Yissakar's \add (Issachar'sВҰ75835)\add* descendantsВҰ75834 came via his sons TolaВҰ75837, PuahВҰ75840,
\v 24 Yashuv, and ShimronВҰ75847.
\v 25 ThoseВҰ75853 clansВҰ75852 added up to 64,300 men.
\s1 Zevulun's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Zebulun
\p
\v 26 Zevulun's descendantsВҰ75862 came via his sons SeredВҰ75865, Eylon, and Yahle'el.
\v 27 ThoseВҰ75877 clansВҰ75876 added up to 60,500 men.
\s1 Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Manasseh
\p
\v 28 Yosef'sВҰ75886 \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants came via his sonsВҰ75885 Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ75888)\add* andВҰ75889 Efrayim.
\v 29 Menashsheh's descendantsВҰ75891 came from his son MakirВҰ75893 andВҰ75896 then his son GileadВҰ75900.
\v 30 Gilead'sВҰ75907 descendantsВҰ75906 came via his sons IezerВҰ75908, HelekВҰ75911,
\v 31 Asriel, Shekem,
\v 32 Shemida, andВҰ75925 HeferВҰ75925.
\v 33 Hefer'sВҰ75932 son Tselofehad had no sonsвҖ”only daughters named MahlahВҰ75945, NoahВҰ75946, HoglahВҰ75947, MilkahВҰ75948, andВҰ75929 Tirtsah.
\v 34 ThoseВҰ75953 clansВҰ75952 added up to 52,700 men.
\s1 Efrayim's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Ephraim
\p
\v 35 Efrayim's descendantsВҰ75963 came via his sons ShutelahВҰ75967, BekerВҰ75970, and TahanВҰ75973,
\v 36 Shutelah'sВҰ75979 descendantsВҰ75978 came via his son EranВҰ75980.
\v 37 Those clans added up to 32,500 men. TheseВҰ75984 last twoВҰ75990 totals were \add all\add* Yosef'sВҰ75998 \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants.
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Benjamin
\p
\v 38 Benyamin'sВҰ76003 descendantsВҰ76002 came via his sons BelaВҰ76005, AshbelВҰ76008, Ahiram,
\v 39 Shefufam, and HufamВҰ76018.
\v 40 Bela'sВҰ76025 descendantsВҰ76023 came via his sons ArdВҰ76026 andВҰ76027 NaamanВҰ76027.
\v 41 ThoseВҰ76037 clansВҰ76038 added up to 45,600 men.
\s1 Dan's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Dan
\p
\v 42 Dan'sВҰ76050 descendantsВҰ76048 came via his son ShuhamВҰ76052.
\v 43 ThatВҰ76063 clan had 64,400 men.
\s1 Asher's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Asher
\p
\v 44 Asher'sВҰ76073 descendantsВҰ76072 came via his sons Yimnah, YishviВҰ76078, and BeriahВҰ76081.
\v 45 Beriah'sВҰ76086 descendantsВҰ76085 came via his sons Hever and MalkielВҰ76090.
\v 46 Asher'sВҰ76097 daughterВҰ76095 was named SerahВҰ76098.
\v 47 ThoseВҰ76104 clansВҰ76101 added up to 53,400 men.
\s1 Naftali's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Naphtali
\p
\v 48 Naftali'sВҰ76114 descendantsВҰ76113 came via his sons Yahtse'el, GuniВҰ76119,
\v 49 Yetser, and ShillemВҰ76126.
\v 50 ThoseВҰ76132 clans added up to 45,400 men.
\s1 The census total and the division of land
\rem /s1 The Census Results
\p
\v 51 TheВҰ76144 total of all those tribes counted came to 601,730 men.\f + \fr 26:51 \ft Slightly smaller than the total of 603,550 from the first census, see \xt 1:46.\f*
\p
\v 52 Then YahwehВҰ76156 told MoshehВҰ76159,\x + \xo 26:52-56: \xt Num 34:13; Josh 14:1-2.\x*
\v 53 вҖңThe land should be allocated to those \add clans\add* according to the numberВҰ76166 of their namesВҰ76167, to become their inheritanceВҰ76165.
\v 54 Those with largerВҰ76169 numbers should receive more, andВҰ76172 the smallerВҰ76172 groups receive less, \add i.e.,\add* each inheritance \add вүҲdepends on the number of family members\add*.
\v 55 \add вүҲYou must throw\add* lots to determine \add вүҲwhich clan gets which piece of land\add*. \add вүҲThe lands of the clans must be within theirВҰ76191 tribal lands\add*.
\v 56 \add вүҲThen the size of the area that will become\add* their inheritanceВҰ76199 mustВҰ76198 be apportioned according to the \add вүҲcensus numbers\add*.
\s1 Levi's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Levi
\p
\v 57 The listed LevitesВҰ76207 included the clansВҰ76208 \add from Levi's sons\add* GershonВҰ76209, KohatВҰ76212, andВҰ76205 MerariВҰ76215,
\v 58 which were the Livnites, the Hevronites, the Mahlites, the Mushites, andВҰ76233 the Korahites. \add вүҲAlso,\add* Korah fatheredВҰ76234 AmramВҰ76237
\v 59 \add *whose\add* wifeВҰ76241 was Levi'sВҰ76246 daughterВҰ76244 Yokeved who'd been born inВҰ76251 EgyptВҰ76251. \add #They\add* had two sons Aharon \add (AaronВҰ76256)\add* and MoshehВҰ76259 \add (MosesВҰ76259)\add*, and theirВҰ76262 \add older\add* sisterВҰ76262 Miryam \add (MiriamВҰ76261)\add*.
\v 60 Aharon's \add вүҲsons were\add* Nadav, Avihu, EleazarВҰ76274, andВҰ76264 ItamarВҰ76277,\x + \xo 26:60: \xt Num 3:2.\x*
\v 61 \add вүҲbutВҰ76279\add* Nadav andВҰ76281 Avihu had diedВҰ76279 when they'd offeredВҰ76282 YahwehВҰ76287 \add вүҲfireВҰ76283 inВҰ76282 a disobedient manner\add*.\x + \xo 26:61: \xt Lev 10:1-2; Num 3:4.\x*
\v 62 The maleВҰ76296 \add Levites\add* who were a monthВҰ76299 old or older came to 23,000, butВҰ76289 they weren't \add вүҲincluded in the above nation-wide count\add* becauseВҰ76301 they \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ76303 inheritВҰ76313 land in the same way as other tribes\add*.
\s1 Census summary
\p
\v 63 Those were the \add вүҲcensus results from when\add* MoshehВҰ76320 andВҰ76321 the priestВҰ76322 EleazarВҰ76321 counted the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76327\add* on the Moav plainsВҰ76329 \add вүҲon the east side of\add* the Yarden river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 64 \add вүҲNone of the men on those lists were on the previous lists done\add* by MoshehВҰ76341 andВҰ76342 the priestВҰ76343 Aharon when they'd countedВҰ76340 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76348\add* inВҰ76335 the SinaiВҰ76351 wildernessВҰ76350,
\v 65 becauseВҰ76366 YahwehВҰ76356 had told them that they'd certainly die \add there\add* inВҰ76360 the wildernessВҰ76360 until none of \add @those alive\add* were left other than Yefunneh'sВҰ76372 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ76369)\add* and Nun'sВҰ76376 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.
\c 27
\s1 Inheritances without sons
\rem /s1 The Daughters of Zelophehad; Zelophehad's Daughters
\p
\v 1 Then the daughters of Tselofehad (son of HeferВҰ76384, son of GileadВҰ76387, son of MakirВҰ76390, son of Menashsheh) approachedВҰ76379. \add *Their\add* namesВҰ76400 were MahlahВҰ76402, NoahВҰ76403, HoglahВҰ76404, Milkah, and Tirtsah.
\v 2 They stoodВҰ76408 \add вүҲin frontВҰ76409 of\add* MoshehВҰ76410 and the priestВҰ76413 EleazarВҰ76412 and all the leadersВҰ76415 and the people \add there\add* at the entranceВҰ76419 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ76420\add* tentВҰ76420, \add and\add* \add вүҲasked\add*,
\v 3 вҖңOur fatherВҰ76425 died inВҰ76427 the wildernessВҰ76427, \add вүҲalthough\add* he wasn't \add вүҲpart of the group who joined KorahВҰ76440 to rebel\add* against YahwehВҰ76437вҖ”it was \add вүҲfor his own personal disobedience\add* thatВҰ76434 he died. He didn'tВҰ76429 have any sonsВҰ76445
\v 4 \add but\add* why should his family nameВҰ76453 disappear from our clan \add just\add* becauseВҰ76458 he had no sons? \add So\add* giveВҰ76462 us \add вүҲsome land like\add* our father'sВҰ76455 relatives will be getting.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ76470\add* MoshehВҰ76471 took their case to YahwehВҰ76477
\v 6 andВҰ76480 \add *he\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ76480\add*,
\v 7 вҖңIt's right what Tselofehad's daughtersВҰ76488 are saying. You mustВҰ76492 give them \add вүҲsome land like their father's relatives will be getting\add*. \add вүҲGive them whatever would have been given to their father as his\add* inheritance.
\v 8 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ76509,\add* tell the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ76508\add* that if a manВҰ76512 dies \add вүҲwithout sons\add*, thenВҰ76506 his inheritanceВҰ76522 should go to his daughter(s).
\v 9 If he had no \add вүҲchildren\add*, thenВҰ76525 \add вүҲit should go\add* to his brothersВҰ76534,
\v 10 and if he has no brothers, then \add вүҲit should go\add* to his father'sВҰ76547 brothers.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if his fatherВҰ76553 had no brothersВҰ76552, thenВҰ76549 the inheritanceВҰ76557 \add вүҲshould go to his nearestВҰ76559 blood-relative to become his possessionВҰ76562\add*. That will \add вүҲbecome a permanent regulationВҰ76567\add* for YisraelВҰ76566, just as YahwehВҰ76571 has commandedВҰ76570.вҖқ
\s1 Yehoshua succeeds Mosheh
\rem /s1 Joshua to Succeed Moses; Joshua Chosen to Lead Israel; Joshua Is Chosen as Successor to Moses; Joshua Appointed Moses' Successor
\r (Deu. 31:1-8)
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ76578 told MoshehВҰ76581 \add (MosesВҰ76581)\add*, вҖңGo up MtВҰ76585. Avarim and look at the land thatВҰ76592 I'veВҰ76593 givenВҰ76593 to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76594\add*,\x + \xo 27:12-14: \xt Deu 3:23-27; 32:48-52.\x*
\v 13 and thenВҰ76597 you'll \add вүҲdie and join your ancestors\add* just like your brotherВҰ76609 AharonВҰ76608 \add вүҲdid\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲThat's because back\add* in the Tsin wilderness when the \add вүҲpeople complained about water\add*, you two rebelledВҰ76612 againstВҰ76612 my \add вүҲcommandВҰ76613 and failed to respect my holinessВҰ76619\add* in front of them. That was \add when you struck the rock\add* atВҰ76614 MeribahВҰ76625 \add near\add* KadeshВҰ76626 in the Tsin wilderness.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Then MoshehВҰ76633 \add вүҲrequested\add* YahwehВҰ76636,
\v 16 вҖңYahwehВҰ76640, \add you\add* \add вүҲare the godВҰ76641 who directs the spiritsВҰ76642 of all humankind\add*, \add so please\add* appointВҰ76639 a \add вүҲnew leader for the Israeli people\add*
\v 17 who will \add вүҲstand in front of\add* them and lead them out and bringВҰ76661 them in \add вүҲso\add* \add *they\add* won'tВҰ76662 be like sheepВҰ76666 without a shepherdВҰ76671.\x + \xo 27:17: \xt 1Ki 22:17; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ76673 YahwehВҰ76674 told MoshehВҰ76677, вҖңGet Nun'sВҰ76686 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*, a manВҰ76687 who has \add &my\add* spiritВҰ76690 in him, andВҰ76673 place yourВҰ76695 hands on him \add to indicate the transfer of leadership\add*.\x + \xo 27:18: \xt Exo 24:13.\x*
\v 19 Stand him in frontВҰ76700 of the priestВҰ76702 EleazarВҰ76701 and all the assembly, and \add вүҲcommissionВҰ76707 him as they watch\add*.
\v 20 GiveВҰ76720 him some of yourВҰ76712 authorityВҰ76712 so that all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ76719\add* peopleВҰ76719 can hearВҰ76715 \add <it\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ76722\add* \add he needs guidance\add*, he mustВҰ76725 standВҰ76725 \add вүҲin frontВҰ76730\add* of the priestВҰ76724 EleazarВҰ76723 and ask for Yahweh's decisionВҰ76728 \add to be given via\add* the Urim. ThenВҰ76722 \add @Yehoshua\add* and all the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ76743\add* will goВҰ76735 in or comeВҰ76739 out as per \add @Yahweh's\add* \add вүҲinstructions\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 27:21: \xt Exo 28:30; 1Sam 14:41; 28:6.\x*
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ76751\add* MoshehВҰ76752 did what YahwehВҰ76755 had orderedВҰ76754 him to, and he \add вүҲpresented\add* YehoshuaВҰ76760 to the priestВҰ76764 EleazarВҰ76763 and to the entireВҰ76766 community.
\v 23 \add @Mosheh\add* placedВҰ76770 his handsВҰ76773 onВҰ76779 \add @Yehoshua\add* andВҰ76770 \add вүҲcommissionedВҰ76775\add* himВҰ76775, just has YahwehВҰ76778 had said \add *he\add* should.
\c 28
\s1 The daily offerings
\rem /s1 The Regular Offerings; The Daily Offerings; Daily Offerings
\r (Exo. 29:38-46)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ76785 told MoshehВҰ76788 \add (MosesВҰ76788)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңGive the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76794\add* \add <these instructions\add*: Ensure that youВҰ76796 presentВҰ76806 to me the offerings \add and\add* food for offerings to be burnt atВҰ76808 the \add вүҲproper\add* timeВҰ76808.
\v 3 ForВҰ76816 the \add вүҲdaily\add* burntВҰ76824 offering, present twoВҰ76822 one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76817 thatВҰ76814 have noВҰ76821 defectsВҰ76821.
\v 4 One of those lambs mustВҰ76831 be offered in the morningВҰ76832, andВҰ76833 the other in \add вүҲlate afternoon\add*,
\v 5 \add each offeredВҰ76843\add* along with a kilogram of fine flourВҰ76842 mixedВҰ76844 with a litre of \add olive\add* oilВҰ76845.
\v 6 That's the regular burntВҰ76850 offering done like the first one atВҰ76853 MtВҰ76853. SinaiВҰ76854вҖ”the soothingВҰ76856 aromaВҰ76855 from the fireВҰ76857 will be pleasingВҰ76856 to YahwehВҰ76858.
\v 7 The drink offering must \add also\add* be one litre for each lambВҰ76863. That strongВҰ76868 drink must be poured out inВҰ76865 the sacred area as an offering to YahwehВҰ76869.
\v 8 \add вүҲAt the end of the afternoon,\add* offer the secondВҰ76873 lambВҰ76872 with the same-sized offerings of flour andВҰ76879 wine as in the morningВҰ76878. \add вүҲWhenВҰ76871 they're burnt,\add* the aromaВҰ76882 will be pleasingВҰ76883 to YahwehВҰ76884.
\s1 The Rest Day offerings
\rem /s1 The Sabbath Offerings; The Sabbath Offering; Sabbath Offerings
\p
\v 9 вҖңOn the Rest Day, \add it must be\add* two one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76891 with noВҰ76895 defectsВҰ76895, along with 2 kilograms of fine flourВҰ76898 mixedВҰ76900 with oilВҰ76901, as well as the drinkВҰ76902 offering.
\v 10 That will be burnt every Rest Day, inВҰ76906 addition to the regularВҰ76910 \add daily\add* burnt offering and its drinkВҰ76911 offering.
\s1 The new month offerings
\rem /s1 Monthly Offerings; The Monthly Offerings; The Offering on the First Day of the Month
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲOn the first day of each monthВҰ76915\add*, you all mustВҰ76916 bringВҰ76916 YahwehВҰ76918 a burntВҰ76917 offeringВҰ76917 of twoВҰ76923 young bullsВҰ76919, one ram, and sevenВҰ76930 one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76926 withВҰ76914 noВҰ76931 defectsВҰ76931.
\v 12 Each bullВҰ76939 must be offered with threeВҰ76933 kilograms of fine flour mixed with oil, each ram with twoВҰ76941 kilograms,
\v 13 andВҰ76950 each lambВҰ76956 with one kilogram. \add All of that\add* will be a burntВҰ76958 offering with an aromaВҰ76959 that will be pleasingВҰ76960 to YahwehВҰ76962.
\v 14 Their \add respective\add* drinkВҰ76964 offeringsВҰ76964 will be two litres of wine with the bullВҰ76968, 1.3 litres with the ram, andВҰ76964 one litre with each lambВҰ76974. That will be the burntВҰ76977 offeringВҰ76977 \add вүҲfor the start of each new\add* monthВҰ76980 throughoutВҰ76980 the yearВҰ76981.
\v 15 In additionВҰ76983 to those burntВҰ76990 offerings andВҰ76993 drinkВҰ76993 offerings, a maleВҰ76983 goatВҰ76983 mustВҰ76992 \add also\add* be presented to YahwehВҰ76987 as a sinВҰ76986 offering.
\s1 The вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ offerings
\rem /s1 The Passover; Offerings for the Passover; The Offerings at the Festival of Unleavened Bread; Offerings at Passover
\r (Lev. 23:5-14)
\p
\v 16 вҖңYahweh'sВҰ77003 вҖҳpassoverВҰ77002вҖҷ \add ceremony will start\add* onВҰ76996 the 14th of the firstВҰ76997 month \add (Nisan = March/April) each year\add*.\x + \xo 28:16: \xt Exo 12:1-13; Deu 16:1-2.\x*
\v 17 The 15th will be \add the start of\add* the celebrationвҖ”\add вүҲall your breadВҰ77013 mustВҰ77005 be made without any rising agent\add*.\x + \xo 28:17-25: \xt Exo 12:14-20; 23:15; 34:18; Deu 16:3-8.\x*
\v 18 That firstВҰ77017 day, there's to be a sacredВҰ77020 assemblyВҰ77018. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\v 19 YouВҰ77031 all mustВҰ77028 offer twoВҰ77036 \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77032, one ram, andВҰ77028 sevenВҰ77039 one-year-old lambsВҰ77040 with noВҰ77043 defectsВҰ77043 to be burntВҰ77030 on the fireВҰ77029.
\v 20 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77047 offeringsВҰ77047 mustВҰ77057 be threeВҰ77051 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77048 mixedВҰ77049 withВҰ77050 \add olive\add* for the bullВҰ77053, twoВҰ77054 kilograms for the ram,
\v 21 \add and\add* one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77064 lambsВҰ77065.
\v 22 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ77067,\add* bring one maleВҰ77067 goatВҰ77067 as a sinВҰ77068 offeringВҰ77068 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 23 Those offerings mustВҰ77079 be \em in additionВҰ77073\em* to the regularВҰ77078 morningВҰ77075 offerings
\v 24 \add and\add* mustВҰ77085 be offered for each of the sevenВҰ77087 daysВҰ77088. The aromaВҰ77091 of those burnt offerings will be pleasingВҰ77093 to YahwehВҰ77094, along with the regularВҰ77098 burnt offering and its drinkВҰ77100 offering.
\v 25 On the seventhВҰ77103 day, there's to be \add another\add* sacredВҰ77106 assemblyВҰ77104. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\s1 Harvest festival offerings
\rem /s1 The Offerings at the Harvest Festival; Offerings for the Festival of Harvest; Feast of Weeks; Offerings at the Festival of Weeks
\r (Lev. 23:15-22)
\p
\v 26 вҖңOn the firstfruitsВҰ77118 day of the harvest festival, when you all presentВҰ77119 an offeringВҰ77120 of fresh grainВҰ77120 to YahwehВҰ77122, there's to be a sacredВҰ77126 assemblyВҰ77124. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.\x + \xo 28:26-31: \xt Exo 23:16; 34:22; Deu 16:9-12.\x*
\v 27 You all mustВҰ77136 present a burntВҰ77137 offeringВҰ77137 that's a pleasingВҰ77139 aromaВҰ77138 for YahwehВҰ77140, \add presenting\add* twoВҰ77145 \add young\add* bullsВҰ77141, one ram, andВҰ77136 sevenВҰ77148 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77149.
\v 28 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77153 offeringsВҰ77153 will be threeВҰ77157 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77154 mixedВҰ77155 withВҰ77156 \add olive\add* oilВҰ77156 for each bullВҰ77159, twoВҰ77161 kilograms for the ram,
\v 29 and one kilogram for each of the lambsВҰ77171.
\v 30 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77173 goatВҰ77173 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 31 Those offerings along with theirВҰ77188 drink offerings mustВҰ77183 be offered in additionВҰ77179 to the regularВҰ77181 burntВҰ77180 offering and drink offerings. Ensure that they have noВҰ77184 defectsВҰ77184.
\c 29
\s1 The trumpeting celebration
\rem /s1 Offerings at the Festival of Trumpets; The Offerings at the New Year Festival; Feast of Trumpets; Offerings for the Festival of Trumpets
\r (Lev. 23:23-25)
\p
\v 1 вҖңOn the firstВҰ77193 day of the seventhВҰ77192 month \add (Tishrei = September/October) each year\add*, there's to be a sacredВҰ77197 assemblyВҰ77195. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that dayвҖ”it'll be a day of blowingВҰ77207 horns.
\v 2 You all mustВҰ77211 present a \add вүҲyoung\add* bullВҰ77216, a ram, andВҰ77211 sevenВҰ77227 one-year-old lambsВҰ77223, \add all\add* with noВҰ77228 defectsВҰ77228 as a burntВҰ77212 offeringВҰ77211 to be a pleasingВҰ77214 aromaВҰ77213 for YahwehВҰ77215.
\v 3 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77230 offeringВҰ77230 will be threeВҰ77234 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77231 mixedВҰ77232 with \add olive\add* oilВҰ77233 with the bullВҰ77236, twoВҰ77237 kilograms with the ram,
\v 4 andВҰ77241 one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77245 lambsВҰ77246.
\v 5 \add AlsoВҰ77248\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77248 goatВҰ77248 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 6 Those are in additionВҰ77256 to the monthly and regularВҰ77261 \add daily\add* burnt offerings with their \add associated\add* grain offerings and drinkВҰ77263 offerings. The aromaВҰ77265 of those burnt offerings will be pleasingВҰ77266 to YahwehВҰ77268.
\s1 The sacrifice for forgiveness
\rem /s1 Offerings for the Day of Atonement; The Offerings at the Day of Atonement; Offerings on the Day of Atonement; Day of Atonement
\r (Lev. 23:26-32)
\p
\v 7 вҖңEach year on the 10th of this seventhВҰ77273 monthВҰ77272 \add (Tishrei = September/October)\add*, there's to be a sacredВҰ77277 assemblyВҰ77275. \add вүҲDon'tВҰ77287 eat any food or doВҰ77288 any regular workВҰ77286 on that day\add*.\x + \xo 29:7-11: \xt Lev 16:29-34.\x*
\v 8 You all mustВҰ77290 presentВҰ77290 a \add вүҲyoung\add* bullВҰ77295, a ram, andВҰ77290 sevenВҰ77306 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77302 as a burntВҰ77291 offeringВҰ77291 that will be a pleasingВҰ77294 aromaВҰ77293 for YahwehВҰ77292. Ensure that theyВҰ77308 have noВҰ77307 defectsВҰ77307.
\v 9 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77311 offeringsВҰ77311 will be threeВҰ77315 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77312 mixedВҰ77313 withВҰ77314 \add olive\add* oilВҰ77314 for the bullВҰ77317, twoВҰ77318 kilograms for the ram,
\v 10 and one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77327 lambsВҰ77328.
\v 11 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77330 goatВҰ77330, in additionВҰ77335 to the one to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add* and the regularВҰ77339 burntВҰ77338 offerings with theirВҰ77341 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77340 and drinkВҰ77341 offerings.
\s1 Offerings during the celebration in shelters
\rem /s1 Offerings at the Festival of Booths; The Offerings at the Festival of Shelters; Feast of Tabernacles; Offerings for the Festival of Shelters
\r (Lev. 23:33-44)
\p
\v 12 вҖңOn the 15th of that seventh monthВҰ77347, there's to be \add another\add* sacredВҰ77351 assemblyВҰ77349. No \add вүҲregular\add* workВҰ77356 may be done that dayВҰ77346 \add which will begin\add* sevenВҰ77363 daysВҰ77364 of celebrationВҰ77360.\x + \xo 29:12-38: \xt Lev 23:34; Deu 16:13-15.\x*
\v 13 вҖңYou all mustВҰ77366 presentВҰ77366 thirteen \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77372, twoВҰ77379 rams, fourteen one-year-old male lambsВҰ77380 as a burntВҰ77367 offering that will be a pleasingВҰ77370 aromaВҰ77369 for YahwehВҰ77371. Ensure that theyВҰ77387 have noВҰ77386 defectsВҰ77386.
\v 14 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77389 offeringsВҰ77389 will be threeВҰ77393 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77390 mixedВҰ77391 withВҰ77392 \add olive\add* oilВҰ77392 for each bullВҰ77395, two kilograms for each ram,
\v 15 andВҰ77407 one kilogram for each of the seven lambsВҰ77414.
\v 16 \add AlsoВҰ77416\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77416 goatВҰ77416 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77421 to the regularВҰ77423 burntВҰ77422 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77424 andВҰ77425 drinkВҰ77425 offerings.
\p
\v 17 вҖңOn the secondВҰ77429 dayВҰ77428, you all must offer twelve \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77430, two rams, fourteen one-year-old male lambsВҰ77438 withoutВҰ77444 defectsВҰ77444,
\v 18 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77446 and drinkВҰ77447 offeringsВҰ77446 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 19 \add AlsoВҰ77454\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77454 goatВҰ77454 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77459 to the regularВҰ77461 burntВҰ77460 offerings with theirВҰ77463 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77462 andВҰ77454 drinkВҰ77463 offerings.
\p
\v 20 вҖңOn the thirdВҰ77467 dayВҰ77466, \add the sacrifice will be\add* eleven youngВҰ77468 bullsВҰ77468, twoВҰ77473 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77474 withoutВҰ77480 defectsВҰ77480,
\v 21 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77482 and drinkВҰ77483 offeringsВҰ77482 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 22 \add AlsoВҰ77490\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77490 goatВҰ77490 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77493 to the regularВҰ77495 burntВҰ77494 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77496 andВҰ77490 drinkВҰ77497 offerings.
\p
\v 23 вҖңOn the fourth dayВҰ77500, \add the sacrifice will be\add* tenВҰ77503 youngВҰ77502 bullsВҰ77502, twoВҰ77505 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77506 withoutВҰ77512 defectsВҰ77512,
\v 24 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77514 and drinkВҰ77515 offeringsВҰ77514 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 25 \add AlsoВҰ77522\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77522 goatВҰ77522 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77527 to the regularВҰ77529 burntВҰ77528 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77530 andВҰ77531 drinkВҰ77531 offerings.
\p
\v 26 вҖңOn the fifthВҰ77535 dayВҰ77534, \add the sacrifice will be\add* nineВҰ77537 youngВҰ77536 bullsВҰ77536, twoВҰ77539 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77540 withoutВҰ77546 defectsВҰ77546,
\v 27 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77548 and drinkВҰ77549 offeringsВҰ77548 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 28 \add AlsoВҰ77556\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77556 goatВҰ77556 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77559 to the regularВҰ77561 burntВҰ77560 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77562 andВҰ77556 drinkВҰ77563 offerings.
\p
\v 29 вҖңOn the sixthВҰ77567 dayВҰ77566, \add the sacrifice will be\add* eightВҰ77569 youngВҰ77568 bullsВҰ77568, twoВҰ77571 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77572 withoutВҰ77578 defectsВҰ77578,
\v 30 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77580 and drinkВҰ77581 offeringsВҰ77580 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 31 \add AlsoВҰ77588\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77588 goatВҰ77588 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77591 to the regularВҰ77593 burntВҰ77592 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77594 andВҰ77595 drinkВҰ77595 offerings.
\p
\v 32 вҖңOn the seventh dayВҰ77598, \add the sacrifice will be\add* sevenВҰ77601 youngВҰ77600 bullsВҰ77600, twoВҰ77603 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77604 withoutВҰ77610 defectsВҰ77610,
\v 33 and theirВҰ77618 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77612 and drinkВҰ77613 offeringsВҰ77612 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 34 \add AlsoВҰ77620\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77620 goatВҰ77620 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77623 to the regularВҰ77625 burntВҰ77624 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77626 andВҰ77627 drinkВҰ77627 offerings.
\p
\v 35 вҖңOn the eighthВҰ77631 \add and final\add* day, there's to be \add another\add* sacred assemblyВҰ77632. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\v 36 You all mustВҰ77642 presentВҰ77642 a youngВҰ77648 bullВҰ77648, a ram, andВҰ77642 sevenВҰ77656 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77652, \add all\add* unblemishedВҰ77657, as a burntВҰ77643 offering that will be a pleasingВҰ77646 aromaВҰ77645 for YahwehВҰ77647.
\v 37 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77659 and drinkВҰ77660 offeringsВҰ77659 must be \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 38 \add AlsoВҰ77667\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77667 goatВҰ77667 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77670 to the regularВҰ77672 burntВҰ77671 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77673 andВҰ77667 drinkВҰ77674 offerings.
\p
\v 39 вҖң\add The above are the regulations for what\add* you all mustВҰ77677 do for YahwehВҰ77678 atВҰ77679 the appointedВҰ77679 timesВҰ77679, inВҰ77679 additionВҰ77680 to your vows and voluntary offerings, burntВҰ77683 offerings, grainВҰ77684 and drinkВҰ77685 offerings, and your peaceВҰ77686 offerings.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 \add вүҲSo\add* Moses passed on to the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* everything that Yahweh had instructed \add *him\add*.
\c 30
\s1 Instructions about vows
\rem /s1 Rules about Vows; Vows Made by Women; Vows; Laws concerning Vows
\p
\v 1 Then Mosheh \add (MosesВҰ77690)\add* \add вүҲgave\add* the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ77693 leaders\add* \add вүҲthese further instructionsВҰ77698 from\add* YahwehВҰ77699,
\v 2 вҖңIf a man makes a solemn promise to YahwehВҰ77719, or makes a binding vow on his own life, he mustn't dishonour \add вүҲwhat he said\add*вҖ”he must follow whatever came out of his mouth.\x + \xo 30:2: \xt Deu 23:21-23; Mat 5:33.\x*
\p
\v 3 If a \add вүҲyoung\add* woman who is \add вүҲstill living with her parents\add* solemnly promises to YahwehВҰ77727 \add <to doВҰ77744 something\add*,
\v 4 and \add вүЎif\add* her fatherВҰ77756 hears her make the binding vow onВҰ77757 her life and he remains silent, then her vow and \add вүҲall her obligationsВҰ77754\add* will stand.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if her father forbids her \add вүҲwhen\add* he hearsВҰ77760 her, then thatВҰ77766 vow and \add вүҲits obligationsВҰ77780\add* won't stand, and Yahweh will forgive her, because her father \add вүҲstepped in\add*.
\p
\v 6 IfВҰ77809 sheВҰ77803 \add вүҲgets engaged or married while a vow or thoughtless promise still holds\add*,
\v 7 and her \add (future)\add* husbandВҰ77824 hears about it and remains silent thatВҰ77830 day, then her vow and or thoughtless promise will stand.
\v 8 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if her \add (future)\add* husbandВҰ77838 forbids her \add вүҲwhen\add* he hearsВҰ77840 her, then thatВҰ77846 vow and \add вүҲits obligationsВҰ77845\add* won't stand, and Yahweh will forgive her.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲIfВҰ77875\add* a widow or a woman who has been divorced \add вүҲmakes a promise, she mustВҰ77859 do what she promised\add*.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲIf a married woman\add* makes a solemn promise, or makes a binding vow on herВҰ77890 own life,
\v 11 and her husbandВҰ77898 hears about it \add вүҲbutВҰ77895\add* says nothing and doesn't forbid her, then her vow and \add вүҲall her obligationsВҰ77903\add* will stand.
\v 12 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if he actually nullifies it when he hears about it, any promise thatВҰ77924 she pronounced or binding vow on her life, won'tВҰ77914 stand. HerВҰ77920 husbandВҰ77911 has nullified them and Yahweh will forgive her,
\v 13 \add so\add* every vow and its obligationsВҰ77947 can either be nullifiedВҰ77952 or confirmed by herВҰ77946 husband.
\v 14 If herВҰ77970 husbandВҰ77970 has stayed silent for \add вүҲseveral days\add*, that will confirmВҰ77969 all her vows and/or obligationsВҰ77965 because he \add вүҲsaid nothing\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if he \add вүҲcancels\add* them \add sometime\add* after he'd heardВҰ78005 about them, then he will bear herВҰ77989 guilt.
\p
\v 16 Those are the instructions that Yahweh \add вүҲgave\add* Mosheh \add about promises\add* between a man and his wife, \add and\add* between a father and his \add вүҲunmarried\add* daughter \add вүҲliving at home\add*.
\c 31
\s1 Avenging the Midyanites
\rem /s1 Vengeance on the Midianites; Conquest of the Midianites; The Holy War against Midian; War against Midian
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ78042 told MoshehВҰ78045 \add (MosesВҰ78045)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңAvengeВҰ78048 the Midyanites for what they did to \add you\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ78050\add*. After that, you'll \add вүҲgo to join yourВҰ78058 ancestors\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ78060\add* MoshehВҰ78061 told the peopleВҰ78064, вҖңEquip some of your menВҰ78068 to battleВҰ78069 against Midyan to \add вүҲexecuteВҰ78074\add* Yahweh'sВҰ78077 vengeanceВҰ78075 onВҰ78078 \add *them\add*вҖ”
\v 4 one thousand men from each tribeВҰ78085 to go to war.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ78092\add* a thousand men were conscriptedВҰ78090 from each tribeВҰ78094вҖ”twelve thousand equippedВҰ78099 for battleВҰ78100
\v 6 andВҰ78102 MoshehВҰ78104 sentВҰ78102 them off to war. The priestВҰ78115 Pinehas (Eleazar'sВҰ78114 son) went with them, taking some sacredВҰ78118 objects as well as the signal trumpetsВҰ78119.
\v 7 ThenВҰ78123 they foughtВҰ78123 MidyanВҰ78126 just as YahwehВҰ78129 had commandedВҰ78128 MoshehВҰ78132, andВҰ78133 they killedВҰ78133 everyВҰ78134 maleВҰ78136.
\v 8 \add Among them,\add* they killed five Midyan kings: Evi, RekemВҰ78151, TsurВҰ78154, HurВҰ78157, andВҰ78138 Reva, inВҰ78170 additionВҰ78138 to Beor'sВҰ78168 son Bileam \add (BalaamВҰ78165)\add*.
\p
\v 9 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ78175\add* took the Midyan womenВҰ78178 and children captiveВҰ78172, and took all their cattleВҰ78186, \add вүҲsheep and goats\add*, and all their \add вүҲpossessions as plunderВҰ78197\add*,
\v 10 thenВҰ78199 theyВҰ78208 burntВҰ78208 down all their citiesВҰ78202 and houses and campsВҰ78207.
\v 11 They tookВҰ78211 all the spoilВҰ78216 and plunderВҰ78220 includingВҰ78217 the peopleВҰ78221 and animals back,
\v 12 and broughtВҰ78224 it to MoshehВҰ78227 and the priestВҰ78231 EleazarВҰ78230, and to the \add вүҲassembled IsraelisВҰ78235\add* who were \add all still\add* camped on the Moav plainsВҰ78252 beside the Yarden river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\s1 Purifying the returning warriors
\rem /s1 The Army Returns; Return from the War
\p
\v 13 MoshehВҰ78262 and the priestВҰ78264 EleazarВҰ78263 and all the \add вүҲIsraeli\add* leadersВҰ78267 left the campВҰ78273 to meet them,
\v 14 \add вүҲbutВҰ78275\add* MoshehВҰ78276 was angryВҰ78275 at the top army leaders who were coming back from the battleВҰ78286.
\v 15 вҖңWhyВҰ78290 did you allow all the women to liveВҰ78291?вҖқ \add *he\add* asked them.
\v 16 вҖңThey're the \add вүҲvery ones who did what\add* Bileam \add (BalaamВҰ78302)\add* \add вүҲsuggested to urge the people to be unfaithfulВҰ78305\add* to Yahweh atВҰ78301 PeorВҰ78311, \add вүҲleading to\add* the plagueВҰ78313 \add that struck\add* Yahweh'sВҰ78306 \add вүҲpeople\add*.\x + \xo 31:16: \xt Num 25:1-9.\x*
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ78317 now,\add* kill all the \add вүҲboys\add* plusВҰ78323 everyВҰ78319 womanВҰ78325 who's \add вүҲslept withВҰ78322 a man\add*вҖ”
\v 18 \add вүҲspare only the youngВҰ78333, unmarried girls\add* for yourselvesВҰ78342.
\p
\v 19 вҖңThenВҰ78344 everyoneВҰ78351 who's killedВҰ78351 someoneВҰ78352 or touchedВҰ78355 a dead body must stay outsideВҰ78346 the camp for seven daysВҰ78349. On the thirdВҰ78359 day, you all must purifyВҰ78357 yourselvesВҰ78357, andВҰ78344 \add again\add* onВҰ78356 the seventh day \add butВҰ78344 this timeВҰ78349\add* includingВҰ78353 your captivesВҰ78363.
\v 20 \add AlsoВҰ78365,\add* youВҰ78382 all mustВҰ78382 purifyВҰ78382 all your clothes, plusВҰ78368 anything \add else\add* made of leather or goats' hairВҰ78376 or wood.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Then the priestВҰ78387 EleazarВҰ78386 toldВҰ78399 the \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ78390\add* who'd gone to battleВҰ78393, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ78400 has instructedВҰ78399 MoshehВҰ78403:
\v 22 Only the goldВҰ78408, silverВҰ78411, bronzeВҰ78414, iron, tin, and lead,
\v 23 must pass through fire to make it вҖҳcleanВҰ78434вҖҷ. NeverthelessВҰ78435, it must still be purifiedВҰ78438 with the \add special\add* purifying water, along with anything thatВҰ78428 wouldn't \add вүҲhandle\add* the fire.
\v 24 On the seventhВҰ78451 dayВҰ78450, you all mustВҰ78448 wash your clothesВҰ78449 and thenВҰ78448 you'll be вҖҳcleanВҰ78452вҖҷ and \add вүҲbe allowed to reenter\add* the campВҰ78457.
\s1 Dividing the plunder
\rem /s1 Division of the Spoils; Division of the Loot; Disposition of Captives and Booty; Dividing the Spoils
\p
\v 25 Then YahwehВҰ78461 told MoshehВҰ78464 \add (MosesВҰ78464)\add*,
\v 26 вҖңYou and the priestВҰ78476 EleazarВҰ78475 and the \add вүҲtribal leaders\add* must \add вүҲlist all\add* the plunder \add вүҲincludingВҰ78473 both\add* humanВҰ78472 and animals that were taken captiveВҰ78471.
\v 27 ThenВҰ78481 youВҰ78481 mustВҰ78481 divideВҰ78481 \add *it all\add* out \add equally between the two groups\add*: thoseВҰ78486 who wentВҰ78488 out to battleВҰ78489, andВҰ78490 all \add the rest of\add* the communityВҰ78493.
\v 28 \add вүҲSet asideВҰ78495\add* a tributeВҰ78496 for YahwehВҰ78497 from \add the plunder of\add* the \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ78499\add* who fought in the battleВҰ78502: one from every five-hundred \add captive\add* people, and \add вүЎthe same\add* from the cattleВҰ78512 and donkeysВҰ78515, and from the \add вүҲsheepВҰ78518 and goats\add*.
\v 29 Half of that mustВҰ78521 be given to the priestВҰ78524 EleazarВҰ78523 as the contributionВҰ78525 to YahwehВҰ78526.
\v 30 ThenВҰ78528 from the half \add of the plunder\add* \add given\add* to the \add вүҲcommunity\add*, takeВҰ78532 one from every fiftyВҰ78539 \add captive\add* peopleВҰ78529, and \add вүЎthe same\add* from the cattleВҰ78545 and donkeysВҰ78548, and from the \add вүҲsheepВҰ78551 and goats\add* and other animals. That'sВҰ78531 to be given to the LevitesВҰ78557 because they're the ones who look after Yahweh'sВҰ78561 residence.вҖқ
\v 31 \add вүҲSoВҰ78563\add* Mosheh andВҰ78565 the priestВҰ78566 EleazarВҰ78565 did what YahwehВҰ78569 had toldВҰ78568 them to do.
\p
\v 32 The remainingВҰ78576 plunderВҰ78579 \add after the slaughter of the boys andВҰ78574 the married women\add* from what the warriors had brought back was: 675,00 sheepВҰ78582,
\v 33 72,000 cattleВҰ78593,
\v 34 61,000 donkeysВҰ78598,
\v 35 andВҰ78603 32,000 girls \add вүҲwho hadn't been married\add*.
\v 36 The \add вүҲwarriors who'd fought\add* got: 337,500 sheepВҰ78627,
\v 37 \add вүҲless\add* 675 that were given to YahwehВҰ78641 \add as his tributeВҰ78640\add*.
\v 38 The cattleВҰ78650 were 36,000 \add вүҲless\add* 72 for YahwehВҰ78655.
\v 39 There were 30,500 donkeysВҰ78659 \add вүҲless\add* Yahweh'sВҰ78665 tributeВҰ78664 of sixty-one.
\v 40 The \add вүҲgirls andВҰ78669 young women\add* were 16,000 \add вүҲless\add* 32 for YahwehВҰ78675.
\v 41 \add вүҲSoВҰ78680\add* Mosheh gaveВҰ78680 Yahweh'sВҰ78686 contributionВҰ78685 to the priestВҰ78688 EleazarВҰ78687 as Yahweh had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ78690\add* Mosheh.
\p
\v 42 TheВҰ78698 half for the \add вүҲcommunity\add* thatВҰ78699 MoshehВҰ78701 had dividedВҰ78700 off from the \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ78704\add*
\v 43 was: 337,500 sheepВҰ78712,
\v 44 36,000 cattleВҰ78724,
\v 45 30,500 donkeysВҰ78729,
\v 46 andВҰ78735 16,000 \add вүҲgirls who hadn't been married\add*.
\v 47 From that half for the \add вүҲcommunity\add*, Mosheh tookВҰ78741 one from every fiftyВҰ78753 peopleВҰ78744 and animals, and gaveВҰ78760 it to the LevitesВҰ78762 who serve in Yahweh'sВҰ78766 tentВҰ78765, just as Yahweh had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ78768\add* Mosheh.
\p
\v 48 ThenВҰ78774 the \add вүҲtop army\add* officersВҰ78778 (the commanders over thousands, andВҰ78784 the commanders over hundredsВҰ78785), went to MoshehВҰ78777
\v 49 and \add вүҲinformed\add* \add *him\add*, вҖң\add WeВҰ78790,\add* yourВҰ78791 servantsВҰ78791 have \add вүҲcounted the soldiers who were under us,\add* and \add вүҲnone of our menВҰ78796 are\add* missingВҰ78802,
\v 50 \add вүҲso\add* we've broughtВҰ78806 an offeringВҰ78809 to Yahweh: everyВҰ78811 man who foundВҰ78813 \add вүҲsomething\add* goldВҰ78816 \add like\add* an armletВҰ78817 or braceletsВҰ78818, signetВҰ78819 ring or earringВҰ78820, or necklacesВҰ78821 \add has donated it\add* to \add вүҲmake us right with\add* Yahweh.вҖқ
\v 51 \add вүҲSoВҰ78829\add* MoshehВҰ78830 andВҰ78831 the priestВҰ78832 EleazarВҰ78831 tookВҰ78829 those \add вүҲcrafted\add* goldВҰ78835 itemsВҰ78838 from them,
\v 52 and the totalВҰ78843 contributionВҰ78846 of goldВҰ78845 \add вүҲoffered\add* to YahwehВҰ78849 by the commanders of thousandsВҰ78852 and of hundreds \add вүҲweighed around 190 kilograms\add*.
\v 53 Each of the \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ78865\add* had takenВҰ78867 \add вүҲtheir own\add* plunderВҰ78867,
\v 54 and MoshehВҰ78872 and the priestВҰ78874 EleazarВҰ78873 tookВҰ78871 the goldВҰ78877 from the commandersВҰ78879 of thousandsВҰ78880 and of hundredsВҰ78881, and broughtВҰ78882 it to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ78886\add* tentВҰ78886 as a memorialВҰ78888 for the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ78889\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ78892\add* of YahwehВҰ78893.
\c 32
\s1 The tribes who stayed east of Yarden
\rem /s1 The Tribes East of the Jordan; Conquest and Division of Transjordan; The Transjordan Tribes
\r (Deu. 3:12-22)
\p
\v 1 The \add people\add* from the Reuven and GadВҰ78904 \add вүҲtribes\add* \add had amassed\add* \add вүҲa lot of\add* livestock, and theyВҰ78907 \add вүҲnoticedВҰ78907\add* that the YazerВҰ78911 and GileadВҰ78915 \add вүҲregionsВҰ78910\add* \add вүҲwere very suitable\add* for livestock.
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ78921\add* \add *their leaders\add* wentВҰ78921 to MoshehВҰ78930 and the priestВҰ78934 EleazarВҰ78933 and the \add вүҲcommunityВҰ78938 leaders\add* to say,
\v 3 \add The regions of\add* Atarot, DivonВҰ78942, YazerВҰ78943, NimrahВҰ78944, HeshbonВҰ78945, ElealehВҰ78946, Sevam, Nevo, and BeonВҰ78949
\v 4 are \add in\add* the land \add here\add* thatВҰ78952 YahwehВҰ78954 has \add вүҲhanded over to\add* \add вүҲus IsraelisВҰ78956\add*. It'sВҰ78957 \add ideal\add* for livestock, and \add we,\add* yourВҰ78961 servantsВҰ78961, \add вүҲraise\add* livestock.
\v 5 If we've \add вүҲearnt\add* your favourВҰ78969, let this land be givenВҰ78971 to your servantsВҰ78976 for \add вүҲus to ownВҰ78977\add*, \add rather than forcing us\add* to crossВҰ78980 over the Yarden \add river withВҰ78970 all the other tribes\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңIt wouldn't be right for your \add вүҲfellow Israelis\add* to goВҰ78993 to war \add вүҲwhile\add* you all \add just\add* stay here,вҖқ MoshehВҰ78986 told them.
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ78999\add* why doВҰ79000 youВҰ79000 discourageВҰ79000 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ79005 enthusiasm\add* for crossing over into the land thatВҰ79011 YahwehВҰ79015 has givenВҰ79013 them?
\v 8 Your parents didВҰ79018 that atВҰ79020 Kadesh-Barnea when I sentВҰ79020 them \add inВҰ79020\add* to \add вүҲsurvey\add* the land.\x + \xo 32:8-9: \xt Num 13:17-33.\x*
\v 9 They wentВҰ79029 as far as the Eshkol \add вүҲvalley\add* andВҰ79029 they sawВҰ79034 the land, \add вүҲyet\add* they discouragedВҰ79038 the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ79042 from\add* entering the land thatВҰ79050 YahwehВҰ79054 had givenВҰ79052 them.
\v 10 YahwehВҰ79059 \add вүҲgot very angry\add* that dayВҰ79060, andВҰ79062 \add вүҲpromised\add*,
\v 11 вҖҳFrom the menВҰ79068 who cameВҰ79069 out of EgyptВҰ79070, no man who's twentyВҰ79072 or older will seeВҰ79067 the land whichВҰ79077 I promised to AbrahamВҰ79079, Yitshak \add (IsaacВҰ79080)\add*, and Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*, becauseВҰ79082 they're not \add вүҲfully with\add* me.
\v 12 \add вүҲOnly\add* Yefunneh'sВҰ79092 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ79089)\add* andВҰ79094 Nun'sВҰ79097 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add* \add will enter\add* becauseВҰ79098 theyВҰ79099 \add вүҲhave believed\add* me.вҖҷ
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ79103\add* Yahweh \add вүҲgot angry withВҰ79107\add* YisraelВҰ79107, andВҰ79108 made \add вүҲus\add* wanderВҰ79108 inВҰ79107 the wildernessВҰ79109 for fortyВҰ79110 years untilВҰ79112 thatВҰ79118 generationВҰ79117 was \add вүҲeliminated\add* who had \add вүҲbeen evilВҰ79119 as per Yahweh'sВҰ79106 judgement\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲNow look here!\add* You're \add вүҲstanding in front of me\add* \add just\add* like your parentsвҖ”a broodВҰ79127 of \add вүҲdisobedient\add* peopleВҰ79128 who'll make YahwehВҰ79136 more angry with you than he was with your parents!
\v 15 If you all turnВҰ79142 away from followingВҰ79143 himВҰ79143, he'll \add вүҲabandonВҰ79146\add* you all inВҰ79147 the wildernessВҰ79147 againВҰ79145, and you will have destroyedВҰ79148 this \add вүҲnation\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever, theyВҰ79157 stepped\add* closer to him and saidВҰ79157, вҖң\add First\add* we'll build pens for our animals, and build citiesВҰ79163 for our \add вүҲfamilies\add* \add here\add*.
\v 17 ThenВҰ79166 we'll equipВҰ79167 ourselvesВҰ79167 for war, \add вүҲto go ahead of the rest\add* of YisraelВҰ79171 untilВҰ79172 we've broughtВҰ79176 them into theirВҰ79179 placeВҰ79179. \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* ourВҰ79181 \add вүҲfamilies\add* will live in those fortifiedВҰ79183 citiesВҰ79182 because \add вүҲthere'll still be threats from\add* those who live in \add вүҲthis region\add*.
\v 18 WeВҰ79196 won't returnВҰ79189 to ourВҰ79192 \add вүҲhomesВҰ79192\add* untilВҰ79193 everyВҰ79197 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ79195\add* is in possession of his inheritanceВҰ79194.
\v 19 We won'tВҰ79201 take any land \add there\add* on the otherВҰ79204 side of the Yarden \add river\add* or beyondВҰ79206 becauseВҰ79207 this \add вүҲwill be\add* ourВҰ79209 inheritanceВҰ79202 here on the easternВҰ79213 side.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңIf you're \add вүҲgoing to doВҰ79221 that\add*,вҖқ MoshehВҰ79218 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ79216\add*, вҖңthen you all mustВҰ79221 equipВҰ79228 yourselvesВҰ79228 to \add вүҲfight battlesВҰ79231 for\add* YahwehВҰ79230,
\v 21 andВҰ79233 all of \add &your\add* \add вүҲarmed warriors\add* mustВҰ79233 crossВҰ79233 the YardenВҰ79240 \add вүҲto serve\add* YahwehВҰ79242 untilВҰ79243 he's drivenВҰ79244 hisВҰ79248 enemiesВҰ79247 out \add ahead of himВҰ79248\add*.
\v 22 \add Once\add* the land is subduedВҰ79250 \add вүҲbefore\add* Yahweh, thenВҰ79250 you all can returnВҰ79255. You'll be free of obligation from Yahweh and from YisraelВҰ79259, and this land \add here\add* will be your possessionВҰ79264 \add вүҲfrom\add* Yahweh.
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever\add*, if you all don'tВҰ79270 \add вүҲhelp the rest of us\add*, you will be disobeying YahwehВҰ79275, andВҰ79276 \add @your disobedience\add* will \add вүҲcatch up with you\add*.
\v 24 \add So go ahead and\add* build your citiesВҰ79285 for your \add вүҲfamilies\add*, and pensВҰ79287 for your flocksВҰ79288, and \add вүҲdoВҰ79291 what you've committed to\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңYour servantsВҰ79303 will doВҰ79304 what you've saidВҰ79293,вҖқ \add вүҲconfirmed\add* the \add leaders of\add* the Reuven andВҰ79297 GadВҰ79296 tribes.
\v 26 вҖңOur wivesВҰ79310 and children, and our livestockВҰ79311 and all our animalsВҰ79314 will remain in citiesВҰ79318 here in the GileadВҰ79319 \add region\add*,
\v 27 \add вүҲbutВҰ79321\add* we'll equipВҰ79325 ourselves for battle andВҰ79321 to crossВҰ79322 \add <the river\add* to battle for YahwehВҰ79328 just as my masterВҰ79331 has spokenВҰ79332.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ79334\add* MoshehВҰ79336 \add вүҲgave instructionsВҰ79334\add* about them to the priestВҰ79339 EleazarВҰ79338, Nun'sВҰ79344 son YehoshuaВҰ79341, andВҰ79334 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ79351 tribal leaders\add*,\x + \xo 32:28-32: \xt Josh 1:12-15.\x*
\v 29 telling them, вҖңIf the \add вүҲmen from GadВҰ79361 and Reuven tribes\add* crossВҰ79358 over the Yarden with you \add вүҲand equippedВҰ79372 ready to fight for\add* YahwehВҰ79375 and that land \add вүҲis conquered\add*, thenВҰ79353 you mustВҰ79358 giveВҰ79379 them the GileadВҰ79384 \add вүҲregionВҰ79383 for them to ownВҰ79385\add*.
\v 30 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if they don'tВҰ79389 crossВҰ79390 over withВҰ79394 \add the rest of\add* you, thenВҰ79387 \add вүҲthey'll have to accept\add* land \add вүҲto own\add* \add there\add* inВҰ79394 Kanaan \add (CanaanВҰ79397)\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖңWhat YahwehВҰ79409 has told you, \add &his\add* servantsВҰ79412, that's what we'll doВҰ79414,вҖқ the \add вүҲleaders of the GadВҰ79402 andВҰ79403 Reuven tribes responded\add*.
\v 32 We'llВҰ79416 \add вүҲsend armed men across\add* to Kanaan, equippedВҰ79418 to fight for YahwehВҰ79420. \add вүҲHowever,\add* ourВҰ79425 inheritanceВҰ79425 to ownВҰ79424 will be \add here\add* on this sideВҰ79426 of the Yarden \add river\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 33 \add вүҲSoВҰ79429\add* MoshehВҰ79432 gaveВҰ79429 \add <that region\add* to the tribesВҰ79440 of ReubenВҰ79437 and GadВҰ79435, the half-tribe of Yosef'sВҰ79445 son Menashsheh, \add encompassing\add* the kingdoms of the AmoriteВҰ79451 King SihonВҰ79449 and the Bashan'sВҰ79457 King OgВҰ79455, plusВҰ79436 the surrounding territoriesВҰ79460.
\v 34 The Gadites rebuiltВҰ79465 DivonВҰ79471, AtarotВҰ79474, AroerВҰ79476,
\v 35 AtrotВҰ79480-ShofanВҰ79481, YazerВҰ79484, YogbehahВҰ79485,
\v 36 Beyt-NimrahВҰ79490, andВҰ79487 Beyt-HaranВҰ79490вҖ”\add all\add* fortifiedВҰ79496 citiesВҰ79495 with pensВҰ79497 for their flocks.
\v 37 The Reuvenites rebuilt HeshbonВҰ79505, ElealehВҰ79508, Kiriatayim,
\v 38 NevoВҰ79514, BaalВҰ79517-MeonВҰ79518, andВҰ79512 SibmahВҰ79523, \add вүҲbutВҰ79512\add* theyВҰ79531 \add вүҲrenamed\add* \add some\add* of the citiesВҰ79529.
\p
\v 39 The descendantsВҰ79534 of Menashsheh's son MakirВҰ79535 wentВҰ79533 to GileadВҰ79539 andВҰ79533 capturedВҰ79540 itвҖ”driving out the AmoritesВҰ79544 who \add вүҲlived there\add*.
\v 40 \add вүҲSoВҰ79549\add* MoshehВҰ79550 gaveВҰ79549 GileadВҰ79553 to Menashsheh'sВҰ79557 son MakirВҰ79554, andВҰ79558 \add his clan\add* lived there.
\v 41 Menashsheh's \add other\add* son Yair wentВҰ79565 and capturedВҰ79566 \add @the Amorite\add* villages and named them вҖҳYair'sВҰ79573 TownsвҖҷ \add (or вҖҳHavvot-YairвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 42 \add A man named\add* Novah wentВҰ79576 and capturedВҰ79577 KenatВҰ79580 and its villagesВҰ79583, and renamed it to вҖҳNovahвҖҷ after himself.
\c 33
\s1 The journey legs from Egypt to Sinai
\rem /s1 The Journey from Egypt to Moab; The Stages of Israel's Journey from Egypt; Stages in Israel's Journey; Remembering Israel's Journey
\p
\v 1 \add @The following\add* are \add the details\add* of the \add вүҲstages of Yisrael's journeysВҰ79591\add* \add starting from\add* when theyВҰ79596 exited EgyptВҰ79598 \add вүҲtribe-by-tribe\add* under MoshehВҰ79602 and Aharon's leadershipВҰ79600.
\v 2 MoshehВҰ79606, \add вүҲacting on Yahweh'sВҰ79614 instructions\add*, had written down their \add вүҲdeparture points\add*, so theseВҰ79615 were \add the legs of\add* their journeysВҰ79610:
\p
\v 3 The day afterВҰ79628 \add they celebrated\add* the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add вүҲ(around the end of March)\add*, they leftВҰ79619 RamesesВҰ79620 city, raising \add вүҲone fist\add* inВҰ79621 full view of all EgyptВҰ79639 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add*, the Egyptians were buryingВҰ79642 all their oldest sons who'd been struckВҰ79645 down by YahwehВҰ79646 \add вүҲwho had\add* \add also\add* \add вүҲtotally humiliated\add* their godsВҰ79651.
\p
\v 5 After leaving RamesesВҰ79660, the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ79659\add* \add went\add* to Sukkot andВҰ79661 campedВҰ79661 \add there\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ79664 they leftВҰ79664 SukkitВҰ79665 andВҰ79666 campedВҰ79666 at EtamВҰ79667 at the edge of the wildernessВҰ79670.
\v 7 \add вүҲAfter\add* EtamВҰ79673, they turnedВҰ79674 back to Pi-Hahirot (opposite Baal-Tsefon) andВҰ79672 campedВҰ79685 \add вүҲfacing\add* Migdal.
\v 8 ThenВҰ79689 they leftВҰ79689 Pi-HahirotВҰ79691 and walked through the middleВҰ79693 of the seaВҰ79695 into the EtamВҰ79702 wilderness and campedВҰ79703 atВҰ79693 MarahВҰ79704.
\v 9 From MarahВҰ79707, they wentВҰ79708 to Eylim which had twelve springsВҰ79713 withВҰ79710 seventyВҰ79715 palmВҰ79716 treesВҰ79716 \add around them\add*, andВҰ79706 they campedВҰ79717 thereВҰ79719.
\v 10 \add вүҲAfter\add* Eylam, they campedВҰ79723 beside the Red Sea
\v 11 before leaving the seaВҰ79731 and camping in the SinВҰ79737 wilderness.\f + \fr 33:11 \ft Note that this is located in the southwestern Sinai Peninsula (between Eylim and Mt. Sinai), and different from the Tsin \+add (Zin)\+add* wilderness (which is located in the northern Negev desert, near Kadesh-Barnea).\f*
\v 12 \add вүҲTravellingВҰ79742 from there,\add* they campedВҰ79743 atВҰ79744 DofkahВҰ79744,
\v 13 andВҰ79748 thenВҰ79746 from there, atВҰ79749 AlushВҰ79749.
\v 14 \add вүҲAfter leaving\add* AlushВҰ79752, they campedВҰ79753 atВҰ79754 RefidimВҰ79754 \add butВҰ79751\add* they didn'tВҰ79755 have waterВҰ79759 thereВҰ79758 to drinkВҰ79761.
\v 15 \add вүҲWhenВҰ79763\add* they leftВҰ79763 RefidimВҰ79764, they campedВҰ79765 inВҰ79766 the SinaiВҰ79767 wildernessВҰ79766.
\s1 The journey legs in the wilderness
\p
\v 16 From the SinaiВҰ79771 wildernessВҰ79770, they went to Kivot-Hattaavah andВҰ79772 campedВҰ79772 \add there\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲWhenВҰ79776\add* they leftВҰ79776 Kivot-Hattaavah, they campedВҰ79779 atВҰ79780 Hatserot,
\v 18 andВҰ79784 thenВҰ79782 from there, atВҰ79785 RitmahВҰ79785.
\v 19 From RitmahВҰ79788, they \add went to\add* RimmonВҰ79790-Perets to camp,
\v 20 andВҰ79796 after that, onВҰ79797 to LivnahВҰ79797.
\v 21 ThenВҰ79799 they leftВҰ79799 LivnahВҰ79800 andВҰ79801 campedВҰ79801 atВҰ79802 RissahВҰ79802,
\v 22 \add вүҲbefore moving onВҰ79807 from there to\add* camp atВҰ79807 KehelatahВҰ79807.
\v 23 From KehelatahВҰ79810, they campedВҰ79811 atВҰ79812 MtВҰ79812. SheferВҰ79814,
\v 24 thenВҰ79816 they leftВҰ79816 \add *the mountain\add* andВҰ79820 campedВҰ79820 atВҰ79821 HaradahВҰ79821.
\v 25 \add вүҲWhenВҰ79823\add* they leftВҰ79823 HaradahВҰ79824, they campedВҰ79825 atВҰ79826 MakhelotВҰ79826,
\v 26 andВҰ79830 after that, onВҰ79831 to TahatВҰ79831.
\v 27 From TahatВҰ79834, they campedВҰ79835 atВҰ79836 TerahВҰ79836,
\v 28 andВҰ79840 thenВҰ79838 from TerahВҰ79839, they went to MitkahВҰ79841 to camp.
\v 29 \add вүҲAfter\add* MitkahВҰ79844, they campedВҰ79845 atВҰ79846 HashmonahВҰ79846,
\v 30 andВҰ79850 \add вүҲnext after that\add*, they campedВҰ79850 atВҰ79851 MoserotВҰ79851.
\v 31 ThenВҰ79853 they leftВҰ79853 MoserotВҰ79854 andВҰ79855 campedВҰ79855 atВҰ79856 Bene-Yaakan.
\v 32 From Bene-Yaakan, they \add went to\add* Hor-Haggidgad andВҰ79862 campedВҰ79862 \add there\add*,
\v 33 thenВҰ79866 they leftВҰ79866 andВҰ79869 campedВҰ79869 atВҰ79870 YotbatahВҰ79870.
\v 34 ThenВҰ79872 they leftВҰ79872 Yotbatah andВҰ79874 campedВҰ79874 atВҰ79875 Avronah.
\v 35 From Avronah, they \add went to\add* Etsyon-Gever andВҰ79879 campedВҰ79879 \add there\add*,
\v 36 thenВҰ79883 they leftВҰ79883 andВҰ79886 campedВҰ79886 inВҰ79887 the TsinВҰ79889 \add (ZinВҰ79889)\add* wildernessВҰ79887, i.e., atВҰ79887 KadeshВҰ79891.
\v 37 ThenВҰ79893 they leftВҰ79893 KadeshВҰ79894 andВҰ79893 campedВҰ79895 atВҰ79896 MtВҰ79897. HorВҰ79896 by the borderВҰ79898 withВҰ79896 EdomВҰ79900.
\p
\v 38 Aharon \add (AaronВҰ79903)\add* the priestВҰ79904 \add вүҲclimbed\add* MtВҰ79908. HorВҰ79907 \add вүҲfollowing Yahweh'sВҰ79912 instructions\add*, andВҰ79902 thenВҰ79902 diedВҰ79913 thereВҰ79914 onВҰ79923 the 5th of the firstВҰ79925 month, fortyВҰ79916 years afterВҰ79917 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ79920\add* had left EgyptВҰ79922.\x + \xo 33:38: \xt Num 20:22-28; Deu 10:6; 32:50.\x*
\v 39 \add *He\add* was 123 years old when he diedВҰ79935 \add there\add* onВҰ79935 MtВҰ79937. HorВҰ79936.
\p
\v 40 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the CanaaniteВҰ79941 kingВҰ79942 of AradВҰ79943 who lived in the NegevВҰ79947 in Kanaan, heard that the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ79951\add* were comingВҰ79950.
\p
\v 41 \add @The Israelis\add* leftВҰ79954 MtВҰ79956. HorВҰ79955 andВҰ79957 campedВҰ79957 atВҰ79958 TsalmonahВҰ79958.
\rem /s1 Instructions before Crossing the Jordan
\v 42 \add вүҲWhenВҰ79960\add* they leftВҰ79960 TsalmonahВҰ79961, they campedВҰ79962 atВҰ79963 PunonВҰ79963,
\v 43 andВҰ79967 \add вүҲafter that\add*, onВҰ79968 to Ovot.
\v 44 \add вүҲFrom\add* Ovot, they \add went onВҰ79973\add* to Iyey-Haavarim atВҰ79973 the Moav borderВҰ79975.
\v 45 ThenВҰ79978 they leftВҰ79978 \add *there\add* andВҰ79980 campedВҰ79980 atВҰ79981 DivonВҰ79981-GadВҰ79979,
\v 46 \add вүҲbefore going onВҰ79988 to\add* camp atВҰ79988 Almon-Divlatayim.
\v 47 \add вүҲFrom there,\add* they \add went into\add* the Avarim mountainsВҰ79995 andВҰ79994 campedВҰ79994 \add вүҲfacing\add* Nevo.
\v 48 \add вүҲAfter leaving\add* the Avarim mountainsВҰ80001, they \add вүҲreached\add* the Moav plainsВҰ80004 by the Yarden \add (Jordan) river\add* \add вүҲopposite\add* Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 49 They campedВҰ80010 \add вүҲbeside\add* the \add *river\add* from Beyt-Hayshimot to Avel-Shittim \add there\add* onВҰ80019 the Moav plainsВҰ80019.
\rem /s1 Directions for the Conquest of Canaan
\p
\v 50 Then YahwehВҰ80024 spokeВҰ80023 to MoshehВҰ80027 \add there\add* onВҰ80028 the Moav plainsВҰ80028 beside the Yarden \add вүҲopposite\add* Yeriho,
\v 51 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ80039\add* that you're all aboutВҰ80045 to crossВҰ80045 the Yahweh to enter CanaanВҰ80052.
\v 52 ThenВҰ80054 you all mustВҰ80054 \add вүҲdriveВҰ80054 all the land's inhabitantsВҰ80059 out ahead of you\add*, and destroy all their carvedВҰ80066 images and cast metalВҰ80071 images, and all their \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add*.
\v 53 Take the land from there andВҰ80079 start to live there, becauseВҰ80086 I'veВҰ80088 givenВҰ80088 \add *it\add* to all of you to ownВҰ80079.
\v 54 \add вүҲUse lots\add* to divide the land up for your clansВҰ80100. \add вүҲThe largerВҰ80101 groups mustВҰ80095 get more than the smallerВҰ80106 groups\add*, thenВҰ80095 \add вүҲwhatever the lot gives, that will be the area to be given within the land for that ancestralВҰ80121 tribeВҰ80120\add*.\x + \xo 33:54: \xt Num 26:54-56.\x*
\p
\v 55 If you don'tВҰ80126 \add вүҲdrive out the current inhabitantsВҰ80130\add*, thenВҰ80124 they'll become like barbsВҰ80137 in your eyesВҰ80138 and thornsВҰ80139 in your sidesВҰ80140, and they'll harass you all \add вүҲwhen you live there\add*.
\v 56 \add вүҲIf that happens,\add* thenВҰ80151 I'llВҰ80156 \add вүҲgive you all the punishment\add* that I intendedВҰ80153 for them.вҖқ
\c 34
\s1 The boundaries within Canaan
\rem /s1 Boundaries of Canaan; Boundaries of the Land; The Boundaries of the Land
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ80161 told MoshehВҰ80164 \add (MosesВҰ80164)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTell the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ80170\add* that you're all aboutВҰ80177 to enter CanaanВҰ80181вҖ”the land that will become your inheritanceВҰ80187. \add вүҲThe boundariesВҰ80190 will be\add*:
\p
\v 3 вҖңThe \bd southernВҰ80196\bd* border will extend from the TsinВҰ80199 wildernessВҰ80197 along the EdomВҰ80203 border across to the Salt \add (Dead)\add* Sea on the east,
\v 4 cross south of the Scorpion Pass, continue to TsinВҰ80221, and go south of Kadesh-Barnea. ThenВҰ80214 it will go on to Hatsar-AddarВҰ80231 and proceed to Atsmon,
\v 5 From Atsmon \add itВҰ80235 will extend west\add* to the riverbed at the borderВҰ80236 with EgyptВҰ80239, andВҰ80240 thenВҰ80235 across to the \add Mediterranean\add* Sea.
\p
\v 6 вҖңThe \bd western\bd* borderВҰ80255 will be the \add вүҲMediterranean\add* seaВҰ80248.
\p
\v 7 вҖңThe \bd northernВҰ80263\bd* borderВҰ80262 will start at the \add вүҲMediterranean\add* seaВҰ80266 andВҰ80258 extend west to MtВҰ80271. HorВҰ80270,
\v 8 and then on to Levo-HamatВҰ80277 and onward to TsedadВҰ80281.
\v 9 \add From there\add* the border will extendВҰ80283 to ZifronВҰ80285, andВҰ80283 it will end at Hatsar-Eynan, \add вүҲcompleting\add* the northernВҰ80295 border.
\p
\v 10 вҖңThe \bd easternВҰ80300\bd* borderВҰ80299 will begin at Hatsar-Eynan andВҰ80297 extend \add south\add* to ShefamВҰ80303,
\v 11 then go downhill to Rivlah east of Ayin, then along the \add вүҲhills\add* to the east of Lake Galilee \add (Heb. KinneretВҰ80319)\add*.
\v 12 ThenВҰ80322 the border will extend \add south\add* along the Yarden \add River\add* andВҰ80322 \add вүҲendВҰ80326 at\add* the Salt \add (Dead)\add* Sea.
\p вҖңThose will be your \add вүҲcountry's\add* borders.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ80336 MoshehВҰ80337 \add вүҲcontinued\add*, вҖңThat will be the land thatВҰ80345 \add mustВҰ80346 be distributed\add* by lot. It'll be given by YahwehВҰ80351 as an inheritanceВҰ80346 for the nineВҰ80353 tribesВҰ80354 andВҰ80336 the Menashsheh half-tribe\x + \xo 34:13: \xt Num 26:52-56.\x*
\v 14 \add as\add* the Reuven and GadВҰ80368 tribes and the Menashsheh half-tribe have already received their inheritanceВҰ80375.
\v 15 \add Yes,\add* the \add otherВҰ80383\add* twoВҰ80377 andВҰ80379 a half tribesВҰ80378 have takenВҰ80381 up theirВҰ80382 inheritanceВҰ80382 on the easternВҰ80386 sideВҰ80383 of the Yarden \add river\add* across from Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\s1 The teachers egpepamaaren of land
\rem /s1 Tribal Leaders; Leaders to Divide the Land; The Leaders Responsible for Dividing the Land
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ80391 told MoshehВҰ80394,
\v 17 вҖңTheseВҰ80397 are the menВҰ80399 who will \add вүҲdistribute\add* the land: the priestВҰ80408 EleazarВҰ80407 and Nun'sВҰ80412 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*,
\v 18 as well as one leader from each tribeВҰ80418 to allocate the land that will be their inheritanceВҰ80420.
\v 19 Those \add tribeВҰ80428\add* leaders are:
\li1 From YehudahВҰ80429 \add (Judah)\add*, Yefunneh'sВҰ80433 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ80430)\add*,
\li1
\v 20 From Shimeon, Ammihud'sВҰ80441 son ShemuelВҰ80438,
\li1
\v 21 From BenyaminВҰ80444, Kislon's son ElidadВҰ80445,
\li1
\v 22 From DanВҰ80453, Yogli'sВҰ80458 son BukkiВҰ80455,
\li1
\v 23 From Menashsheh, Efod'sВҰ80470 son Hanniyel,
\li1
\v 24 From Efrayim, Shiftan'sВҰ80480 son KemuelВҰ80477,
\li1
\v 25 From Zevulun, Parnach'sВҰ80490 son ElizafanВҰ80487,
\li1
\v 26 From Yissakar, Azzan'sВҰ80500 son PaltielВҰ80497,
\li1
\v 27 From AsherВҰ80505, Shelomi'sВҰ80510 son AhihudВҰ80507,
\li1
\v 28 From NaftaliВҰ80515, Ammihud'sВҰ80520 son PedahelВҰ80517.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲThe above\add* are \add the men\add* that YahwehВҰ80525 \add вүҲput in charge of dividing up\add* Kanaan as the inheritanceВҰ80526 for the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ80529\add*.
\c 35
\s1 Cities for the Levites
\rem /s1 Towns for the Levites; The Cities Assigned to the Levites; Cities for the Levites
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲWhile\add* they were there onВҰ80541 the Moav plainsВҰ80541 beside the Yarden \add river\add*, YahwehВҰ80537 told MoshehВҰ80540 \add (MosesВҰ80540)\add*.\x + \xo 35:1-8: \xt Josh 21:1-42.\x*
\v 2 вҖңTell the \add IsraelisВҰ80552\add* that out of the land that they'll \add вүҲownВҰ80557\add*, they mustВҰ80554 give the LevitesВҰ80555 cities for them to live in, \add вүҲas well as\add* some pasturelandВҰ80560 aroundВҰ80562 \add &those\add* cities.
\v 3 The citiesВҰ80567 will be for them to liveВҰ80569 in, and that pasturelandВҰ80570 will be for their herds and their flocks, and for their other animalsВҰ80575.
\v 4 The pasturelandВҰ80577 mustВҰ80580 extend out half a kilometre aroundВҰ80587 the walls of the LevitesВҰ80581 citiesВҰ80578.
\v 5 ThenВҰ80589 going out a kilometre \add вүҲin each compass direction\add*, that will also be their land.\f + \fr 35:5 \ft It's not exactly clear what different activities would occur in these two rings of land, but remember that as much food as possible and animals would have to be brought into the city as soon as the residents received news of an approaching army.\f*
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge
\v 6 The LevitesВҰ80631 \add вүҲmust be given forty-two cities to live in, plusВҰ80642\add* you all must \add вүҲdesignate\add* six refuge cities so thatВҰ80629 if someone accidentally kills another, they can flee to the refuge city.
\v 7 \add вүҲThat would make a total of\add* forty-eight citiesВҰ80650, plusВҰ80655 theirВҰ80660 pasturelandsВҰ80660, to be given to the LevitesВҰ80653.
\v 8 The largerВҰ80670 tribes mustВҰ80664 give more cities than the smallerВҰ80673 tribes, accordingВҰ80676 to the area thatВҰ80663 they inheritВҰ80677.вҖқ
\s1 The refuge cities
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge; The Cities of Refuge
\r (Deu. 19:1-13; Josh. 20:1-9)
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ80686 told MoshehВҰ80689,\x + \xo 35:9-28: \xt Deu 19:2-4; Josh 20:1-9.\x*
\v 10 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ80695\add* that when youВҰ80697 crossВҰ80701 the Yarden \add river\add* \add вүҲto enter\add* Kanaan,
\v 11 you all mustВҰ80708 choose some cities to become вҖҳrefugeВҰ80712 citiesвҖҷ \add so that\add* if someone accidentallyВҰ80721 kills another personВҰ80720, they can flee thereВҰ80716.
\v 12 The citiesВҰ80725 will be places to stay safe from \add вүҲbeing avengedВҰ80727\add* \add by the relatives\add* untilВҰ80731 the killerВҰ80730 can \add вүҲbe formally tried\add*.
\v 13 You all mustВҰ80740 \add вүҲallocate\add* six refugeВҰ80744 citiesвҖ”
\v 14 three on the eastern side of the Yarden, and there on the western side in Kanann.
\v 15 BothВҰ80766 \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ80765\add* and \add вүҲforeigners living inВҰ80769 the country\add* can flee to \add any of\add* those sixВҰ80771 citiesВҰ80773вҖ”anyoneВҰ80780 who kills \add another\add* personВҰ80782 by accidentВҰ80783.
\rem /s1 Concerning Murder and Blood Revenge
\p
\v 16 вҖңHowever, if someone strikesВҰ80790 \add @another person\add* withВҰ80787 \add вүҲa metal objectВҰ80787\add* and they dieВҰ80794, thenВҰ80785 that person is a murderer, and murderers mustВҰ80795 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲSimilarly,\add* anyone who strikesВҰ80805 \add @another person\add* when holding a \add rockВҰ80799 or\add* stoneВҰ80799, thenВҰ80798 thatВҰ80801 person is a murderer, andВҰ80798 murderers mustВҰ80803 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲAgain,\add* if someoneВҰ80820 strikesВҰ80822 \add @another person\add* withВҰ80814 a piece of wood, then thatВҰ80818 person is a murderer, and murderers mustВҰ80820 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*.
\v 19 The \add relative who\add* is avengingВҰ80830 the \add spilt\add* bloodВҰ80831 mustВҰ80833 \add вүҲexecute the murdererВҰ80836 as soon as he finds them\add*.
\p
\v 20 вҖңIf someone pushesВҰ80846 \add @another person\add* in hatredВҰ80845, or lies in wait andВҰ80852 thenВҰ80843 throws something atВҰ80845 them,
\v 21 or angrily strikesВҰ80856 them withВҰ80855 their handВҰ80857, and then they dieВҰ80859, \add вүҲit must be regarded as murder,\add* and when the avengerВҰ80865 of their bloodВҰ80866 finds the murderer, he must \add вүҲexecute\add* them.
\p
\v 22 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ80875\add* if someone pushesВҰ80881 \add @another person\add* without any hateful \add intent\add*, or throws something atВҰ80877 them without lyingВҰ80890 inВҰ80877 wait,
\v 23 or drops a rockВҰ80895 without \add вүҲnoticing\add* someoneВҰ80898, and they dieВҰ80898 \add вүҲbutВҰ80902\add* they weren't \add @that person's\add* enemyВҰ80908 and no harm was intended,
\v 24 thenВҰ80914 the community mustВҰ80914 judgeВҰ80914 between the \add вүҲone who killed\add* andВҰ80918 the avengerВҰ80919 \add вүҲof the dead person\add*, in accordance with theseВҰ80923 regulations.
\v 25 \add If the one who killed is declared innocent\add*, thenВҰ80925 the community must rescueВҰ80925 them from the avengerВҰ80931 and returnВҰ80933 them to the refugeВҰ80939 cityВҰ80938 that they'd fled to, and \add вүҲthat accidental killer\add* must liveВҰ80944 thereВҰ80943 untilВҰ80946 after the deathВҰ80948 of the high priestВҰ80949 (who had been anointedВҰ80953 withВҰ80945 sacredВҰ80956 oilВҰ80955).
\v 26 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if they thenВҰ80958 ever left the refugeВҰ80967 cityВҰ80966 that they'd fled to,
\v 27 and the avenger found them outsideВҰ80976 the city boundary, thenВҰ80972 \add вүҲthat relative of the dead person\add* is permitted to kill that person and won'tВҰ80986 be accountable for their blood.
\v 28 \add That's\add* because the \add вүҲone who killedВҰ81004\add* mustВҰ80993 remainВҰ80993 inВҰ80991 that cityВҰ80991 untilВҰ80994 the death of the high priestвҖ”they can only returnВҰ81003 to \add вүҲtheir family home\add* afterВҰ80999 the high priest's death.
\v 29 You all mustВҰ81010 \add follow\add* theseВҰ81011 regulationsВҰ81013 throughВҰ81015 the generationsВҰ81015 no matter where you liveВҰ81017.
\p
\v 30 вҖң\add If\add* someoneВҰ81026 murdersВҰ81029 \add another\add* personВҰ81023, they're to be executed if there's evidenceВҰ81024 from witnesses (\add plural,\add* not just one witness).
\v 31 That sentence \add вүҲcan'tВҰ81038 be changed to a fine andВҰ81038/or a payment to the deceased's family\add*вҖ”\add @the murderer\add* \em mustВҰ81040\em* be executed.
\v 32 \add вүҲSimilarly for the accidental killer who fled to a refugeВҰ81062 cityВҰ81061\add*, they can'tВҰ81054 \add вүҲelect to pay a fine andВҰ81054/or pay compensation\add* in order to be able to returnВҰ81063 \add вүҲhome\add* before the high priest'sВҰ81069 deathВҰ81068.
\v 33 You mustn't profane the land thatВҰ81077 you're all going to \add by tolerating murder\add*, becauseВҰ81080 \add human\add* blood pollutesВҰ81073 the ground, andВҰ81071 you all can'tВҰ81071 \add вүҲrestore the land withВҰ81079 any sacrifice\add*вҖ”only by the blood of the one who shed \add someone else's\add* blood.
\v 34 You mustn't profane the land thatВҰ81107 you'll all be living in becauseВҰ81115 I'll also be living in itВҰ81114, as I will live among \add you\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ81120\add*.вҖқ
\c 36
\s1 Women inheriting property
\rem /s1 Women Who Inherit Property; Marriage of Female Heirs; The Inheritance of Married Women; Inheritance of Zelophehad's Daughters
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* the leaders of the Gilead clansВҰ81137 (\add вүЎGilead was\add* the son of MakirВҰ81133, son of Menashsheh, one of Yosef'sВҰ81139 sons) approached MoshehВҰ81142 and the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ81148\add* leaders
\v 2 and said, вҖңYahweh commanded my master to \add вүҲdistribute\add* the land by lot as an inheritance \add вүҲfor the peopleВҰ81162\add*, and my master was \add also\add* commanded by Yahweh to give our brotherВҰ81172 Tselofehad's inheritance to his daughtersВҰ81173.\x + \xo 36:2: \xt Num 27:7.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ81181, if\add* they \add ended up\add* \add вүҲbeing married by men from other\add* tribes, thenВҰ81175 their inheritance would \add вүҲpass from our tribe to their husbands' tribes, so we'd end up with less land as our tribal\add* inheritance.
\v 4 ThenВҰ81198 when YisraelВҰ81203 celebrates the Jubilee \add Year\add*, thenВҰ81198 thatВҰ81209 inheritance will be addedВҰ81204 to the inheritance of \add @their husbands'\add* tribes, andВҰ81198 be deducted from the inheritance of ourВҰ81214 \add вүҲancestralВҰ81214\add* tribe.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ81218 MoshehВҰ81219 \add вүҲgave a ruling\add* to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ81222\add* \add вүҲin accordance with what YahwehВҰ81227 had toldВҰ81218 him\add*, вҖңThese \add вүҲYosefite men\add* are correct.
\v 6 Yahweh'sВҰ81241 \add вүҲcommandВҰ81240\add* to Tselofehad'sВҰ81243 daughtersВҰ81242 is thatВҰ81238 \add вүҲeach of you may marry whoever you want as long as it's someone from your own\add* tribeВҰ81251.
\v 7 ThatВҰ81273 way, land \add вүҲinВҰ81268 YisraelВҰ81261\add* won'tВҰ81256 \add вүҲmove\add* from tribe to tribe, becauseВҰ81266 \add вүҲitВҰ81258 will always stay as part of\add* the inheritance \add вүҲgiven to that\add* tribe.
\v 8 \add вүҲAny womanВҰ81288 who inherits land can only marry someone from herВҰ81286 own\add* tribeВҰ81280, so that the people will \add always\add* \add вүҲretain ownership of their tribal\add* inheritance.
\v 9 \add &That\add* inheritance mustn't pass from tribe to tribe, butВҰ81297 each \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ81311\add* tribe mustВҰ81299 keep hold of itsВҰ81307 inheritance.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҮ”So Tselofehad'sВҰ81322 daughtersВҰ81321 obeyed what YahwehВҰ81315 had toldВҰ81314 MoshehВҰ81318,
\v 11 and the \add five\add* daughtersВҰ81330 (MahlahВҰ81325, Tirtsah, HoglahВҰ81327, Milkah, and NoahВҰ81329) married their \add вүҲcousins on their father'sВҰ81333 side\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲThe men theyВҰ81343 married\add* were from the Menashsheh tribe (Yosef'sВҰ81342 son), so \add вүҲtheir land continued to belong to their father'sВҰ81351 family and\add* tribe.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲAll the above\add* were the commandsВҰ81354 and regulations thatВҰ81356 YahwehВҰ81358 orderedВҰ81357 MoshehВҰ81361 to tell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ81364\add*, \add while they were camped\add* onВҰ81359 the Moav plainsВҰ81366 beside the Yarden \add river\add* \add вүҲopposite\add* Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
